1
00:00:00,120 --> 00:00:02,400
What do you see here, Demet?

2
00:00:03,320 --> 00:00:04,720
A happy couple.

3
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:06,880
He bought the necklace for her.

4
00:00:07,320 --> 00:00:10,400
You are jealous of Ateş.

5
00:00:10,720 --> 00:00:12,280
One gets jealous of who one loves.

6
00:00:12,680 --> 00:00:15,520
Do you really love Ateş?

7
00:00:16,240 --> 00:00:21,840
Thank goodness you came, Monika. No one else
could have convinced Ateş to return to America.

8
00:00:22,280 --> 00:00:26,320
It is best for him to return to his life
there anyway. We could not convince him.

9
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:31,680
What did I tell you? Do not trust Ateş too
much. Today it is you, tomorrow someone else.

10
00:00:32,760 --> 00:00:33,760
You see now.

11
00:00:34,680 --> 00:00:36,840
Look how his
mood changed when Monika arrived.

12
00:00:37,360 --> 00:00:39,399
You love him deeply, do you not?

13
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:41,360
You cannot let go of him.

14
00:00:41,680 --> 00:00:43,080
Then say it, Mercan.

15
00:00:43,560 --> 00:00:44,880
Do not think beyond this.

16
00:00:45,560 --> 00:00:47,480
You cannot live like this.

17
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:48,560
I cannot.

18
00:00:48,920 --> 00:00:50,840
I do not understand what
Ateş sees in this girl.

19
00:00:50,880 --> 00:00:52,560
Ateş sees nothing in her.

20
00:00:52,800 --> 00:00:54,440
She is the one chasing Ateş.

21
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:57,760
Of course she would chase someone
like Ateş.

22
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:01,360
What is wrong with you? Why are you
still chasing Ateş?

23
00:01:02,080 --> 00:01:04,080
Give Ateş some space.

24
00:01:04,120 --> 00:01:05,600
He does not even look at you.

25
00:01:07,080 --> 00:01:09,680
We found the cemetery Ateş often visits.

26
00:01:09,880 --> 00:01:11,720
Good. Who is it?

27
00:01:11,920 --> 00:01:13,880
A child’s grave named Eylül Aslan.

28
00:01:15,440 --> 00:01:17,520
When
I told you I loved you, you did not answer.

29
00:01:18,080 --> 00:01:19,880
If you loved me so much…

30
00:01:20,200 --> 00:01:21,600
…why did you buy Monika a necklace?

31
00:01:21,840 --> 00:01:23,600
You cannot think clearly out of jealousy.

32
00:01:24,520 --> 00:01:26,480
I told you I love you.

33
00:01:26,680 --> 00:01:28,840
Why would
I buy a necklace for someone I do not like?

34
00:01:28,960 --> 00:01:30,240
Why would I want to go with her?

35
00:01:30,280 --> 00:01:31,520
I bought that necklace for you.

36
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:33,040
I waited for an answer.

37
00:01:33,520 --> 00:01:34,640
One single answer.

38
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:36,440
You cannot run away now.

39
00:01:36,600 --> 00:01:40,040
Did you not see how these eyes look at you?

40
00:01:40,440 --> 00:01:42,840
You finally confessed you love me.

41
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:44,360
I said I do not love you.
You do.

42
00:01:44,760 --> 00:01:46,040
I love you so much.

43
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:48,360
So much.

44
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:50,000
You are fire.

45
00:01:50,840 --> 00:01:52,280
And I am a moth to that fire.

46
00:01:52,920 --> 00:01:54,999
Even when I try to erase you from my mind…

47
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,400
…I cannot cast you out of my heart.

48
00:01:56,880 --> 00:01:59,160
When a moth
finds fire, it becomes immortal.

49
00:02:00,880 --> 00:02:02,400
Our love is immortal like that.

50
