60
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:39,840
I still cannot believe it.

61
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:41,720
Why?

62
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:47,640
For us...

63
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:50,040
You said you loved me.

64
00:04:00,480 --> 00:04:01,680
Mercan Karahan...

65
00:04:07,640 --> 00:04:08,960
You made me so happy.

66
00:04:12,880 --> 00:04:15,720
So, will we be able to hold on?

67
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:27,800
Can a person live without their other half?

68
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:34,840
You are my heartbeat.

69
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:40,800
You are the beloved of my heart.

70
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:06,400
Look at me.

71
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:09,680
Do not be ashamed.

72
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:18,319
In the eyes you avert...

73
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:19,480
in your blushing cheeks...

74
00:05:24,640 --> 00:05:26,440
I see it in everything about you.

75
00:05:29,640 --> 00:05:31,520
Keep looking at me.

76
00:05:32,080 --> 00:05:33,080
All right?

77
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:35,360
Do not take your eyes off me.

78
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:42,480
I cannot give up those
beautiful eyes of yours.

79
00:05:43,440 --> 00:05:45,240
I can never give you up. Did you hear me?

80
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:17,840
Do not go...

81
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:23,600
Let me have my fill of you.

82
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:27,760
I have been
suffering like a soul in torment for days.

83
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:30,600
What if...

84
00:06:30,601 --> 00:06:33,160
what if she does not love me as much as
I love her...

85
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:35,680
I was about to lose hope.

86
00:06:45,280 --> 00:06:46,560
Were you going to give up on me?

87
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:54,880
How could I ever give up on you?

88
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:01,800
That would be asking for the impossible.

89
00:07:08,440 --> 00:07:10,440
You shattered all my certainties.

90
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:13,640
Do you love me that much?

91
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:21,120
Very much.

92
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:25,720
More than you could ever imagine.

93
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:32,760
Boundless.

94
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:36,160
I am in love with you.

95
00:07:38,880 --> 00:07:40,240
I feel the same.

96
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:43,800
You are my daylight.

97
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:51,760
At least
I managed to make you talk, even by force.

98
00:07:55,840 --> 00:07:58,320
I wish I had
not surrendered so quickly myself.

99
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:00,880
I should have made you
suffer a little longer.

100
00:08:02,440 --> 00:08:03,680
A little more?

101
00:08:05,120 --> 00:08:07,360
I was about to die of longing.

102
00:08:10,520 --> 00:08:11,520
God forbid.

103
00:08:11,760 --> 00:08:13,360
Never say things like that again.

104
00:08:30,480 --> 00:08:31,480
That is enough.

105
00:08:34,160 --> 00:08:35,160
Enough of what?

106
00:08:38,040 --> 00:08:40,120
Look at this place, it is a mess.

107
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:47,520
We need to tidy up.

108
00:08:52,480 --> 00:08:53,680
Do not bother.

109
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:55,440
You cannot hide it.

110
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:58,080
Hide what?

111
00:08:59,440 --> 00:09:00,680
Your embarrassment.

112
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:08,720
Both your love and your embarrassment.

113
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:11,720
You cannot hide behind excuses.

114
00:09:12,320 --> 00:09:14,840
In the eyes you avert...

115
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:19,240
in your blushing cheeks...

116
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:22,800
I see it everywhere.

117
00:09:25,520 --> 00:09:26,520
Shame on you.

118
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:28,320
I am not blushing.

119
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:32,720
Shame on you indeed.

120
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:36,920
You look sweeter when you are embarrassed.

121
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:40,440
It suits you so well.

122
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,840
We should tidy up, but...

123
00:09:57,280 --> 00:09:58,280
Leave it to me.

124
00:09:58,640 --> 00:09:59,800
I will take care of it later.

125
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:02,600
What are you doing?

126
00:10:03,760 --> 00:10:05,640
I am taking my bride to her room.

127
00:10:26,680 --> 00:10:28,320
Put me down, your back will hurt.

128
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:43,320
It is not evening yet, I am not sleepy.

129
00:10:45,400 --> 00:10:46,960
I wanted you to rest a little.

130
00:10:57,880 --> 00:10:58,880
I have some work to do.

131
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:10,480
I will gather what we broke and come right
back.

132
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:14,840
You, meanwhile...

133
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,200
rest.

134
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:33,080
I will be right back.

135
00:11:55,960 --> 00:11:56,960
What is going on?

136
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:06,120
Why are you acting like this, brother?

137
00:12:06,560 --> 00:12:08,640
Why are you trying to block our happiness?

138
00:12:09,040 --> 00:12:11,200
I am telling you, Malik
and I love each other.

139
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:14,680
My daughter, I do not trust this man.

140
00:12:15,400 --> 00:12:18,161
I would never give my sister
to someone I don't trust. That is final.

141
00:12:18,440 --> 00:12:20,600
So none of my wishes matter, is that it?

142
00:12:21,560 --> 00:12:22,560
Çiçek, enough.

143
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:24,120
Do not stand up to your brother.

144
00:12:24,400 --> 00:12:25,880
He is thinking of your well being.

145
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:33,680
My daughter, go outside for a bit.

146
00:12:34,160 --> 00:12:36,040
Let me talk to your brother alone.

147
00:12:48,520 --> 00:12:50,040
Berat, my boy.

148
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:52,680
You used to like this boy.

149
00:12:53,280 --> 00:12:54,400
You called him your brother.

150
00:12:56,520 --> 00:12:57,880
That was long ago, mother.

151
00:12:58,480 --> 00:12:59,560
He is no brother of mine.

152
00:13:00,160 --> 00:13:01,280
He is my enemy, if anything.

153
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:07,920
Look at me, are you saying this
because of what's going on with her, or...

154
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:09,680
is there something else?

155
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:11,760
Mother, what else could there be?

156
00:13:12,520 --> 00:13:15,640
That man went behind our backs and set his
eyes on my sister.

157
00:13:16,040 --> 00:13:17,400
Does that fit any notion of honor?

158
00:13:19,640 --> 00:13:24,600
Son, the love between them is not something
fleeting.

159
00:13:25,640 --> 00:13:26,640
Do you understand?

160
00:13:31,560 --> 00:13:34,960
My child’s happiness
comes before everything for me.

161
00:13:40,520 --> 00:13:43,359
With death breathing down my neck...

162
00:13:43,360 --> 00:13:47,200
all I
want is my child to be happy, Berat.

163
00:13:50,280 --> 00:13:54,280
I cannot bear to see my child unhappy.

164
00:13:54,880 --> 00:13:55,880
Do you understand?

165
00:13:57,880 --> 00:14:00,759
Mother, do not talk about death now...

166
00:14:00,760 --> 00:14:03,560
do not scorch my heart.

167
00:14:05,880 --> 00:14:08,360
Look not at
who says it, but at what makes them say it.

168
00:14:32,960 --> 00:14:35,199
We now...

169
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:36,520
We now with him...

170
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,240
Pull yourself together, Mercan.

171
00:14:48,120 --> 00:14:50,680
What is this, acting like a foolish lover?

172
00:14:53,440 --> 00:14:54,440
But we are.

173
00:14:55,880 --> 00:14:57,040
We are foolish lovers.

174
00:14:58,120 --> 00:14:59,120
Yes.

175
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:18,840
I should let Demet know as well.

176
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:23,600
Ateş stopped me from leaving.

177
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:25,960
I finally confessed to him.

178
00:15:36,560 --> 00:15:38,520
I am so glad.

179
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:45,360
Thank you.

180
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:47,480
For everything.

181
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:58,120
Friends are for days like these.

182
00:16:10,800 --> 00:16:12,960
Should I do something like this?

183
00:16:15,040 --> 00:16:16,040
Like this.

184
00:16:18,920 --> 00:16:20,080
No, this did not work either.

185
00:16:24,160 --> 00:16:26,960
No, this does not seem right.

186
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:48,800
No, it did not work. I look like a ghost.

187
00:16:49,440 --> 00:16:51,200
Should I put on some makeup?

188
00:16:54,120 --> 00:16:56,640
Is this really the time for makeup?

189
00:17:04,920 --> 00:17:06,560
But I look like a witch like this.

190
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:17,240
You are beautiful in every state.

191
00:17:17,880 --> 00:17:19,360
You are my favorite view.

192
00:17:22,680 --> 00:17:24,680
When did you get here?

193
00:17:26,040 --> 00:17:27,960
You were moving from ghost to witch.

194
00:17:28,160 --> 00:17:29,160
Somewhere in between.

195
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:30,680
Let me see.

196
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:34,240
You do not look like a witch either.

197
00:17:49,040 --> 00:17:50,080
What is it?

198
00:17:50,880 --> 00:17:52,320
Why are you looking at me like that?

199
00:17:54,840 --> 00:17:57,200
There is something I have wanted to do for
a long time.

200
00:17:58,520 --> 00:17:59,520
What is it?

201
00:18:03,680 --> 00:18:07,439
Well, I was thinking...

202
00:18:07,440 --> 00:18:08,920
Maybe we should go out?

203
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:15,400
I
Would rather stay here, just the two of us.

204
00:18:16,560 --> 00:18:20,200
But that would not work...

205
00:18:21,160 --> 00:18:21,880
Now...

206
00:18:21,881 --> 00:18:24,201
There is something I've
been holding onto for a long time.

207
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:28,640
I mean...

208
00:18:44,800 --> 00:18:46,400
It is not in this box.

209
00:18:47,840 --> 00:18:48,960
It belongs where it belongs.

210
00:18:56,360 --> 00:18:58,320
I thought so too.

211
00:18:59,200 --> 00:19:00,200
Thought what?

212
00:19:01,080 --> 00:19:02,800
Nothing, nothing at all.

213
00:20:28,720 --> 00:20:31,680
The moment I saw this
necklace, I knew it belonged to you.

214
00:20:33,520 --> 00:20:34,520
You look beautiful.

215
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:47,160
Thank you.

216
00:20:48,560 --> 00:20:49,560
It is beautiful.

217
00:20:50,320 --> 00:20:52,640
I
Thought you had bought it for someone else.

218
00:20:53,680 --> 00:20:54,680
What?

219
00:20:55,600 --> 00:20:56,920
How could you think such a thing?

220
00:20:58,200 --> 00:20:59,720
You are everything to me.

221
00:21:01,080 --> 00:21:02,800
There is no one else in my life but you.

222
00:21:03,440 --> 00:21:04,720
And there never will be.

223
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:10,400
What happened?

224
00:21:11,680 --> 00:21:13,160
Why did a shadow fall over your face?

225
00:21:15,120 --> 00:21:16,920
Our families still do not know.

226
00:21:19,040 --> 00:21:20,360
That is the real battle, I think.

227
00:21:22,560 --> 00:21:24,480
What will you do when you learn the truth?

228
00:21:26,160 --> 00:21:27,640
Will you still love me like this?

229
00:21:38,560 --> 00:21:40,360
I have no right to make you live a lie.

230
00:21:42,040 --> 00:21:43,920
I must tell
you everything as soon as possible.

231
00:21:50,680 --> 00:21:53,560
We will walk out of
this battle hand in hand. Do not be afraid.

232
00:21:54,560 --> 00:21:56,560
I did not want to hurt you.

233
00:21:57,920 --> 00:22:00,800
We started this knowing full well how hard
it would be.

234
00:22:06,120 --> 00:22:07,120
I trust myself.

235
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:09,760
And most of all, I trust you.

236
00:22:11,280 --> 00:22:13,080
Our love will overcome all these obstacles.

237
00:22:27,040 --> 00:22:29,160
What if the biggest obstacle is us?

238
00:22:56,160 --> 00:22:57,160
Hello, mom.

239
00:22:58,560 --> 00:23:01,920
My Malik, my son. I’m
waiting for you. When are you coming back?

240
00:23:03,680 --> 00:23:05,160
Mom, I told you before.

241
00:23:05,320 --> 00:23:06,320
I am repeating myself.

242
00:23:06,440 --> 00:23:07,480
I am not going back there.

243
00:23:08,520 --> 00:23:09,520
I’m staying here.

244
00:23:10,400 --> 00:23:11,720
With the girl I love.

245
00:23:12,880 --> 00:23:13,480
Look,

246
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:14,960
I proposed to Çiçek.

247
00:23:18,840 --> 00:23:20,600
I’m expecting your support.

248
00:23:21,160 --> 00:23:26,320
If you stand behind me,
maybe my father will soften as well.

249
00:23:26,960 --> 00:23:29,680
Your father won’t listen to you or to me,

250
00:23:30,440 --> 00:23:32,800
And I don’t approve of
this marriage either.

251
00:23:33,240 --> 00:23:36,040
Besides, there is a promise made here, and
a girl waiting for you.

252
00:23:36,760 --> 00:23:38,320
Mom, I never gave that promise.

253
00:23:38,760 --> 00:23:40,760
So I am not obliged to keep it.

254
00:23:41,720 --> 00:23:43,399
I didn’t promise anything to anyone.

255
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:45,760
And I’m not responsible
for keeping a promise I never made.

256
00:23:46,720 --> 00:23:47,720
Look,

257
00:23:48,120 --> 00:23:49,120
Mom,

258
00:23:49,200 --> 00:23:51,000
I told you before, I’m staying here.

259
00:23:53,040 --> 00:23:54,640
I’m going to stay with the woman I love.

260
00:23:55,920 --> 00:23:57,640
I don’t want to discuss this again.

261
00:23:57,720 --> 00:23:58,760
This is my final decision.

262
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:02,240
Think it over carefully.

263
00:24:02,400 --> 00:24:03,440
This is my final decision.

264
00:24:04,440 --> 00:24:05,440
Tell my father.

265
00:24:06,680 --> 00:24:07,680
All right?

266
00:24:08,640 --> 00:24:09,720
We’ll talk later.

267
00:24:46,600 --> 00:24:47,120
Mercan?

268
00:24:47,121 --> 00:24:48,520
Yes?

269
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:54,320
Saying your name feels so beautiful.

270
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:01,480
It is so innocent.

271
00:25:01,600 --> 00:25:03,200
Do I have the right to do this to her?

272
00:25:09,320 --> 00:25:12,120
There will be
no real marriage until you know everything.

273
00:25:15,280 --> 00:25:16,280
Ateş.

274
00:25:16,360 --> 00:25:17,600
I know.

275
00:25:19,400 --> 00:25:20,400
Just sleep beside me.

276
00:25:23,080 --> 00:25:25,880
I want to fall asleep holding you tonight.

277
00:25:30,720 --> 00:25:31,920
As long as you stay with me.

278
00:27:23,280 --> 00:27:24,520
Good morning.

279
00:27:25,280 --> 00:27:26,840
Good morning.

280
00:27:33,960 --> 00:27:34,960
Stay, do not go.

281
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:38,040
Come, hold me tight.

282
00:27:44,520 --> 00:27:46,240
I want to tell you something.

283
00:27:46,880 --> 00:27:47,880
Speak, my pearl Mercan.

284
00:27:50,000 --> 00:27:51,920
You will always love me like this, right?

285
00:27:54,160 --> 00:27:55,160
Where did that come from?

286
00:27:57,880 --> 00:27:58,880
I do not know.

287
00:27:59,920 --> 00:28:00,960
I just asked.

288
00:28:02,160 --> 00:28:03,480
My Mercan.

289
00:28:03,720 --> 00:28:04,720
My dawn eyed one.

290
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:07,560
I know why you asked.

291
00:28:08,800 --> 00:28:10,160
But our road will be hard.

292
00:28:11,760 --> 00:28:12,960
We both know that.

293
00:28:14,520 --> 00:28:15,920
But remember this.

294
00:28:18,040 --> 00:28:20,480
Until this heart falls silent, it will keep
saying your name.

295
00:28:25,000 --> 00:28:26,000
Mine too.

296
00:28:27,960 --> 00:28:29,680
Hold my hand like this always, all right?

297
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:47,120
Shall we go outside?

298
00:28:48,800 --> 00:28:50,160
I have not had my fill of you yet.

299
00:28:52,960 --> 00:28:53,960
Come on, get up.

300
00:28:55,800 --> 00:28:56,960
It was nice like this though.

301
00:28:57,520 --> 00:29:00,920
The woman I love beside me, a warm bed.

302
00:29:00,960 --> 00:29:02,240
I am quite content.

303
00:29:04,480 --> 00:29:05,640
Stop being lazy.

304
00:29:08,200 --> 00:29:09,800
We will see today with different eyes.

305
00:29:10,760 --> 00:29:12,160
As if everything were new.

306
00:29:13,560 --> 00:29:15,560
You, me.

307
00:29:16,680 --> 00:29:18,680
The garden, the lake.

308
00:29:19,840 --> 00:29:20,840
The trees.

309
00:29:21,360 --> 00:29:22,360
Birdsong.

310
00:29:24,560 --> 00:29:25,679
It will be beautiful, come on.

311
00:29:25,680 --> 00:29:29,560
It will be beautiful, come on, get up.

312
00:29:32,680 --> 00:29:33,840
Get up, I said.

313
00:29:37,200 --> 00:29:38,200
I said get up.

314
00:29:39,280 --> 00:29:41,240
Me, huh? Me?

315
00:29:43,760 --> 00:29:44,976
So you are declaring war on me.

316
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:46,200
Then you will see.

317
00:31:19,520 --> 00:31:21,320
Welcome, my love.

318
00:31:21,360 --> 00:31:22,360
Glad to be here, my love.

319
00:31:23,320 --> 00:31:25,199
My mother agreed to us...

320
00:31:25,200 --> 00:31:28,400
You cannot imagine how happy I am.

321
00:31:34,240 --> 00:31:36,320
Why are you so quiet then?

322
00:31:37,640 --> 00:31:39,440
Is it my brother again?

323
00:31:40,160 --> 00:31:41,880
He will accept it sooner or later.

324
00:31:42,360 --> 00:31:43,440
Do not worry.

325
00:31:44,280 --> 00:31:45,320
Insallah, my love.

326
00:31:46,280 --> 00:31:47,280
Insallah.

327
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:50,440
Just imagine.

328
00:31:50,920 --> 00:31:52,800
Your family, my family.

329
00:31:53,040 --> 00:31:55,719
All together, one big family.

330
00:31:55,720 --> 00:32:00,600
How can I tell that my family doesn't want
this marriage while you are over the moon?

331
00:32:01,200 --> 00:32:02,680
How do I wither that smiling face?

332
00:32:03,640 --> 00:32:04,640
What if?

333
00:32:04,960 --> 00:32:06,200
Will your parents like me?

334
00:32:06,920 --> 00:32:08,960
What kind of question is that, my Çiçek?

335
00:32:09,200 --> 00:32:10,560
Of course they will.

336
00:32:13,320 --> 00:32:16,360
Malik, do you know my biggest dream?

337
00:32:17,120 --> 00:32:19,000
For our children to grow up in a
happy home.

338
00:32:19,760 --> 00:32:21,200
In a big family.

339
00:32:22,280 --> 00:32:24,519
That dream of yours is so beautiful.

340
00:32:24,520 --> 00:32:26,320
All of it will come true, my love.

341
00:32:26,640 --> 00:32:29,800
I will do more than my
best to make it happen.

342
00:32:30,480 --> 00:32:31,480
I promise you.

343
00:32:35,680 --> 00:32:36,680
Oh at last.

344
00:32:37,440 --> 00:32:38,480
I am so happy.

345
00:32:39,240 --> 00:32:40,760
Me too.

346
00:32:45,120 --> 00:32:46,120
My beautiful eyed one.

347
00:32:54,840 --> 00:32:55,840
All right then.
See you.

348
00:32:58,280 --> 00:32:59,920
Have a safe trip.

349
00:33:01,480 --> 00:33:02,560
Goodbye, Ateş.

350
00:33:02,760 --> 00:33:05,080
I was so glad to see you.

351
00:33:06,760 --> 00:33:07,760
My dear Monika.

352
00:33:08,720 --> 00:33:09,880
Take care of yourself.

353
00:33:20,400 --> 00:33:21,960
Have a good flight.

354
00:33:35,600 --> 00:33:36,640
I am freezing.

355
00:33:37,840 --> 00:33:40,840
Who came up with that ridiculous
lie about me going to America with Monika?

356
00:33:44,840 --> 00:33:47,360
I do not know, son. Ask whoever made it up.

357
00:33:48,760 --> 00:33:50,400
I am cold, let us go inside.

358
00:33:51,840 --> 00:33:54,400
Go on, go inside.

359
00:33:58,000 --> 00:33:59,160
Did they really say that?

360
00:34:00,280 --> 00:34:02,120
Mercan believed it was true.

361
00:34:02,560 --> 00:34:03,680
Damn it.

362
00:34:06,080 --> 00:34:07,240
You are acting strange again.

363
00:34:09,040 --> 00:34:10,600
You did not even stand up to Müzeyyen.

364
00:34:11,360 --> 00:34:12,360
You surprise me.

365
00:34:13,440 --> 00:34:14,840
Did Mercan speak up, what happened?

366
00:34:16,960 --> 00:34:18,000
I am very glad.

367
00:34:18,360 --> 00:34:19,400
Especially for myself.

368
00:34:19,920 --> 00:34:23,200
I have talked so much I turned into
Aşık Veysel.

369
00:34:23,680 --> 00:34:25,000
How old do you think I am, Ateş?

370
00:34:32,160 --> 00:34:33,160
Anyway...

371
00:34:35,520 --> 00:34:37,480
How will I tell Mercan the truth?

372
00:34:38,600 --> 00:34:42,080
Slow down. Tell her when
the right time comes.

373
00:34:44,160 --> 00:34:45,320
Is there really a right time?

374
00:34:52,960 --> 00:34:53,960
Here she comes.

375
00:34:59,640 --> 00:35:00,160
Good morning.

376
00:35:00,560 --> 00:35:01,560
Good morning, Ms. Mercan.

377
00:35:01,920 --> 00:35:03,120
What is this, a picnic?

378
00:35:04,880 --> 00:35:06,840
Not exactly.

379
00:35:07,560 --> 00:35:08,840
I prepared a few things.

380
00:35:09,760 --> 00:35:10,480
We have tea as well.

381
00:35:10,481 --> 00:35:12,320
It is freezing, I am cold.

382
00:35:12,600 --> 00:35:13,240
Enjoy your meal.

383
00:35:13,600 --> 00:35:15,881
Love makes people do strange things
in weather like this.

384
00:35:25,880 --> 00:35:26,880
Here you go.

385
00:35:29,120 --> 00:35:30,480
Mercan Karahan.

386
00:35:32,200 --> 00:35:33,200
With pleasure.

387
00:35:33,800 --> 00:35:34,880
Ateş Karahan.

388
00:36:24,240 --> 00:36:26,880
We need to put this into
the financial statement.

389
00:36:27,120 --> 00:36:28,959
You should take a look at it first.

390
00:36:28,960 --> 00:36:30,480
Ms. Zahide, how was the concert?

391
00:36:32,160 --> 00:36:33,160
It was good.

392
00:36:33,240 --> 00:36:35,640
I had a lot of fun, and Mr. Yaşar too...

393
00:36:36,200 --> 00:36:37,520
We already talked about this.

394
00:36:38,400 --> 00:36:39,800
That is what I am saying.

395
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:41,880
I checked tickets again.
Shall we go once more?

396
00:36:45,120 --> 00:36:46,320
We will.

397
00:36:46,400 --> 00:36:49,760
After this busy period passes.

398
00:36:50,200 --> 00:36:52,199
But honestly...

399
00:36:52,200 --> 00:36:53,680
I was surprised to see you like that.

400
00:36:54,960 --> 00:36:58,440
I
Stopped being surprised by people long ago.

401
00:36:58,600 --> 00:36:59,600
I recommend it to you.

402
00:37:00,720 --> 00:37:03,439
Still, seeing those moves...

403
00:37:03,440 --> 00:37:04,960
Your musical knowledge was impressive.

404
00:37:05,280 --> 00:37:07,400
You think you know everything, do you not?

405
00:37:07,640 --> 00:37:08,720
You know everything.

406
00:37:08,880 --> 00:37:10,040
You do everything best.

407
00:37:11,680 --> 00:37:13,760
It is true, I do know everything.

408
00:37:13,800 --> 00:37:15,160
I cannot be modest about it.

409
00:37:15,640 --> 00:37:17,240
I also know how to enjoy life.

410
00:37:17,800 --> 00:37:19,560
Good for you then.

411
00:37:21,400 --> 00:37:22,760
Where is Demet?

412
00:37:27,160 --> 00:37:28,160
I do not know.

413
00:37:28,520 --> 00:37:30,440
You do not know? How do you not know?

414
00:37:30,760 --> 00:37:32,120
I really do not know, brother.

415
00:37:32,640 --> 00:37:34,640
I think something bad
is going on. Do you not?

416
00:37:34,960 --> 00:37:35,760
What does that have to do with anything?

417
00:37:35,880 --> 00:37:36,880
I mean...

418
00:37:41,480 --> 00:37:42,600
Burak.

419
00:37:46,320 --> 00:37:47,320
We need to talk.

420
00:37:53,440 --> 00:37:54,440
There.

421
00:37:55,720 --> 00:37:56,720
All right.

422
00:38:05,680 --> 00:38:08,760
I like saying I told you so. I told you so.

423
00:38:09,880 --> 00:38:12,520
Good, I applaud you.

424
00:38:12,560 --> 00:38:15,239
The all knowing man award goes to you this
year.

425
00:38:15,240 --> 00:38:15,880
Come on then.

426
00:38:16,200 --> 00:38:18,240
With applause, back to your desk,
Mr. Yaşar.

427
00:38:18,320 --> 00:38:20,360
Please go ahead.

428
00:38:45,400 --> 00:38:47,200
It turned out great. Well done.

429
00:38:47,560 --> 00:38:48,560
Enjoy.

430
00:38:48,960 --> 00:38:50,360
I added plenty of cheese.

431
00:38:51,520 --> 00:38:52,616
Look, there are pastries too.

432
00:38:52,640 --> 00:38:53,680
Çiçek made them yesterday.

433
00:38:53,920 --> 00:38:55,400
They taste great, have some.

434
00:39:06,160 --> 00:39:07,160
I love this place.

435
00:39:08,240 --> 00:39:09,960
I never get bored here.

436
00:39:11,840 --> 00:39:13,920
I
Used to come here all the time as a child.

437
00:39:15,600 --> 00:39:17,200
My brother had a bicycle.

438
00:39:19,800 --> 00:39:21,400
He would ride it around here.

439
00:39:22,480 --> 00:39:23,560
I envied him so much.

440
00:39:25,600 --> 00:39:27,160
They would not let me ride.

441
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:30,400
Tahir...

442
00:39:32,440 --> 00:39:33,720
You know who he is.

443
00:39:34,760 --> 00:39:38,760
I vaguely remember him trying to
teach me a few times.

444
00:39:41,440 --> 00:39:43,640
Or maybe I made it up in my head.

445
00:39:49,120 --> 00:39:50,160
Still did not learn?

446
00:39:52,280 --> 00:39:53,280
No.

447
00:39:53,640 --> 00:39:54,640
Is it not funny?

448
00:39:56,200 --> 00:39:57,200
No.

449
00:40:02,840 --> 00:40:03,840
I will teach you.

450
00:40:08,720 --> 00:40:09,840
I will handle it.

451
00:40:10,520 --> 00:40:11,520
Bring it.

452
00:40:43,960 --> 00:40:45,200
This worked out well.

453
00:40:45,760 --> 00:40:46,920
The weather is beautiful too.

454
00:40:49,200 --> 00:40:50,880
I almost left because of you.

455
00:40:51,640 --> 00:40:53,720
If you had not caught
up, I would be in Germany now.

456
00:40:54,800 --> 00:40:55,880
It was not because of me.

457
00:40:57,000 --> 00:40:58,160
Do not make me say it.

458
00:40:59,200 --> 00:41:01,880
Since it came up, let us make a deal.

459
00:41:03,920 --> 00:41:06,480
No leaving me again.

460
00:41:09,880 --> 00:41:13,639
As long as you want...

461
00:41:13,640 --> 00:41:14,640
I will always be here.

462
00:41:16,600 --> 00:41:17,600
Good.

463
00:41:18,120 --> 00:41:19,120
Keep listening like this.

464
00:41:25,600 --> 00:41:27,840
But I cannot promise obedience.

465
00:41:29,320 --> 00:41:31,280
Old habits die hard.

466
00:41:36,480 --> 00:41:37,480
How would I not know?

467
00:41:38,960 --> 00:41:40,920
But I love you like this.

468
00:41:42,440 --> 00:41:43,480
Your sweet stubbornness...

469
00:41:46,920 --> 00:41:48,680
But promise me something too.

470
00:41:49,160 --> 00:41:50,160
Behave yourself.

471
00:41:51,000 --> 00:41:54,200
Do not put yourself in danger and scare me
to death.

472
00:41:55,560 --> 00:41:56,560
And one more thing...

473
00:41:57,600 --> 00:42:00,400
you will not even mention Monika again.

474
00:42:02,440 --> 00:42:05,280
How many times do
I have to say she means nothing to me?

475
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:09,400
I do not know about that anymore.

476
00:42:12,280 --> 00:42:12,920
Ateş...

477
00:42:12,921 --> 00:42:14,920
How can you not remember?

478
00:42:16,720 --> 00:42:19,160
We watched that movie together.

479
00:42:19,680 --> 00:42:22,000
All right, I am so hungry, Ateş.

480
00:42:29,560 --> 00:42:30,680
I was about to lose my mind.

481
00:42:35,320 --> 00:42:36,760
A toast has no sin...

482
00:42:37,680 --> 00:42:39,040
My jealous princess.

483
00:42:43,880 --> 00:42:45,000
Stop, where are you going?

484
00:43:00,040 --> 00:43:01,920
You are not going anywhere.

485
00:43:50,760 --> 00:43:52,400
Come on, eat your pastry.

486
00:43:53,120 --> 00:43:54,440
These two are yours.

487
00:43:55,080 --> 00:43:56,080
Both are mine.

488
00:43:57,360 --> 00:43:58,400
They will all be finished.

489
00:44:01,640 --> 00:44:03,000
Are two not too many for you?

490
00:44:04,800 --> 00:44:07,200
You keep saying I
am thin. What should I do, not eat?

491
00:44:08,800 --> 00:44:09,800
Eat, of course.

492
00:44:10,080 --> 00:44:11,280
Life comes through the throat.

493
00:44:29,440 --> 00:44:31,960
There is no place for
you in Haydar’s world.

494
00:44:33,200 --> 00:44:35,320
And there never will be as long as I live.

495
00:44:36,360 --> 00:44:37,600
Stay away from my family.

496
00:44:39,520 --> 00:44:41,080
The truth will come out one day.

497
00:44:43,240 --> 00:44:46,880
Not truth, power speaks in this family.

498
00:44:49,800 --> 00:44:52,240
Believe me, you do
not want to challenge that power.

499
00:44:57,680 --> 00:45:00,240
Why did you
hide from me that you are Haydar Bey’s son?

500
00:45:01,280 --> 00:45:03,400
Mercan is my closest friend.

501
00:45:04,000 --> 00:45:07,080
Now I have a brand new
secret thanks to you.

502
00:45:07,560 --> 00:45:11,240
Demet, I know you are
angry, but try to understand me.

503
00:45:11,400 --> 00:45:16,480
Imagine growing up without a father
and then learning he exists somewhere.

504
00:45:17,280 --> 00:45:20,120
I am trying to understand.

505
00:45:20,960 --> 00:45:23,479
It must be terrifying, but...

506
00:45:23,480 --> 00:45:28,280
Even I have not
processed it yet, so I could not share it.

507
00:45:28,920 --> 00:45:30,680
No matter what, you should have told me.

508
00:45:31,960 --> 00:45:35,840
I could not burden
you before we even named our relationship.

509
00:45:36,160 --> 00:45:38,760
Then let us name it now.

510
00:45:39,600 --> 00:45:41,720
We should stay friends from now on, Burak.

511
00:45:51,680 --> 00:45:52,960
What does that mean, Demet?

512
00:45:55,880 --> 00:45:57,840
You kept secrets from me.

513
00:45:59,160 --> 00:46:00,560
How can I trust you again?

514
00:46:02,160 --> 00:46:03,160
No.

515
00:46:05,080 --> 00:46:06,080
I cannot.

516
00:46:12,280 --> 00:46:14,080
You should tell everyone as soon
as possible.

517
00:46:15,480 --> 00:46:17,000
Especially Mercan.

518
00:46:19,120 --> 00:46:21,200
I do not like keeping secrets from her.

519
00:46:51,400 --> 00:46:52,720
Good luck.

520
00:46:53,880 --> 00:46:55,200
May ease come your way.

521
00:47:09,560 --> 00:47:10,560
Aunt Binnaz.

522
00:47:13,120 --> 00:47:14,120
Thank you.

523
00:47:15,240 --> 00:47:16,240
For what?

524
00:47:16,480 --> 00:47:17,480
What did I do?

525
00:47:17,880 --> 00:47:19,080
For believing in me and Çiçek.

526
00:47:19,360 --> 00:47:20,920
For believing in our love.

527
00:47:27,080 --> 00:47:28,760
Come here, my son.

528
00:47:32,320 --> 00:47:34,800
You have been with us for two years.

529
00:47:35,920 --> 00:47:37,120
You know me now.

530
00:47:37,360 --> 00:47:37,960
You know who I am.

531
00:47:37,961 --> 00:47:41,840
My children are my most precious treasures.

532
00:47:41,880 --> 00:47:43,360
They are my life.

533
00:47:43,560 --> 00:47:46,080
Nothing is more valuable to me than them.

534
00:47:47,440 --> 00:47:53,440
Since their good for nothing father left, I
have been both mother and father.

535
00:47:55,480 --> 00:47:57,000
Çiçek has chosen her path.

536
00:47:58,800 --> 00:47:59,800
She chose you.

537
00:48:00,880 --> 00:48:03,640
From now on,
my daughter is entrusted to you.

538
00:48:05,080 --> 00:48:08,920
Aunt Binnaz, I carry that trust on my head,
my eyes, my heart.

539
00:48:12,040 --> 00:48:15,000
I will ask for nothing but one promise.

540
00:48:18,120 --> 00:48:21,160
The heart you stole, my daughter’s heart.

541
00:48:22,880 --> 00:48:23,960
You will never break it.

542
00:48:25,640 --> 00:48:31,679
If a single tear falls from my daughter’s
eyes...

543
00:48:31,680 --> 00:48:35,920
these two hands
will be on your collar. Do you understand?

544
00:48:37,360 --> 00:48:39,120
How do you say that where you come from?

545
00:48:39,800 --> 00:48:40,920
Like this where I am from...

546
00:48:44,560 --> 00:48:46,760
That is how. You understand.

547
00:48:47,280 --> 00:48:49,240
Aunt Binnaz, is that even possible?

548
00:48:50,440 --> 00:48:51,840
I promise you.

549
00:48:51,960 --> 00:48:53,760
I will cherish Çiçek more than my own life.

550
00:48:55,120 --> 00:48:57,320
I will love her more than anything.

551
00:48:58,600 --> 00:49:01,120
Just as now, always.

552
00:49:03,120 --> 00:49:07,040
I will never allow a single
strand of a hair on her head to be harmed.

553
00:49:08,760 --> 00:49:10,640
You will have no worries. I promise.

554
00:49:13,560 --> 00:49:16,600
Go on then. May God clear your path.

555
00:49:17,320 --> 00:49:20,360
I will go take care of my work then.

556
00:49:21,080 --> 00:49:23,000
Aunt Binnaz, I am glad you exist.

557
00:49:24,920 --> 00:49:25,920
You too, my son.

558
00:49:26,440 --> 00:49:27,440
Good luck.

559
00:49:27,960 --> 00:49:28,960
To you as well.

560
00:49:33,720 --> 00:49:35,280
My God, do not let us be ashamed.

561
00:49:37,360 --> 00:49:40,360
So your mother allowed Çiçek to marry?

562
00:49:41,040 --> 00:49:42,320
Even against you.

563
00:49:46,440 --> 00:49:47,840
I still cannot believe it, Zehra.

564
00:49:52,640 --> 00:49:54,360
You are the man of that house, Berat.

565
00:49:55,920 --> 00:49:57,160
You are Çiçek’s brother.

566
00:49:57,720 --> 00:49:59,640
Your word matters most.

567
00:50:00,680 --> 00:50:02,840
How do you allow
them to trample over you like this?

568
00:50:06,840 --> 00:50:09,720
So my word means nothing to them.

569
00:50:10,440 --> 00:50:11,640
I understood that clearly.

570
00:50:12,080 --> 00:50:13,080
Very clearly.

571
00:50:15,000 --> 00:50:16,800
I will not care about them anymore.

572
00:50:18,320 --> 00:50:21,080
I will do what I want and live as I please.

573
00:50:21,680 --> 00:50:22,680
Clearly.

574
00:50:27,920 --> 00:50:28,920
Zehra.

575
00:50:29,920 --> 00:50:31,160
We will get married soon.

576
00:50:32,120 --> 00:50:33,360
We will?

577
00:50:34,160 --> 00:50:35,160
Yes.
All right.

578
00:50:36,400 --> 00:50:40,400
If you
insist this much, then let us get married.

579
00:51:00,760 --> 00:51:02,840
I already knew.

580
00:51:10,600 --> 00:51:13,840
I cannot explain how happy and emotional I
am.

581
00:51:14,400 --> 00:51:16,000
I am so happy for you.

582
00:51:18,720 --> 00:51:19,920
It is all over.

583
00:51:20,640 --> 00:51:22,520
So Mercan confessed too.

584
00:51:25,360 --> 00:51:26,720
What does this mean?

585
00:51:27,440 --> 00:51:28,440
What is this state?

586
00:51:31,920 --> 00:51:33,720
I expect an explanation from you, Ateş.

587
00:51:39,720 --> 00:51:41,240
We will talk later, Mother Müzeyyen.

588
00:51:45,160 --> 00:51:46,640
Oh, Ms. Müzeyyen.

589
00:51:48,480 --> 00:51:50,520
What is there to explain, for God’s sake?

590
00:51:51,760 --> 00:51:53,600
The children love each other.

591
00:51:56,040 --> 00:51:57,040
Mother.

592
00:51:57,600 --> 00:51:58,600
Please, enough.

593
00:52:02,280 --> 00:52:03,520
Let it go, my daughter.

594
00:52:05,360 --> 00:52:07,440
Clearly they still cannot digest it.

595
00:52:09,080 --> 00:52:10,640
We should understand them too.

596
00:52:11,760 --> 00:52:13,080
They will get used to it in time.

597
00:52:13,920 --> 00:52:15,040
I will never get used to it.

598
00:52:15,800 --> 00:52:16,800
Never.

599
00:52:17,160 --> 00:52:18,560
This is complete nonsense.

600
00:52:19,120 --> 00:52:20,680
Ateş, how could you do this?

601
00:52:23,080 --> 00:52:24,080
I do not consent either.

602
00:52:24,800 --> 00:52:26,440
I will never consent to such a thing.

603
00:52:26,920 --> 00:52:28,920
Who are you for your permission to matter?

604
00:52:29,520 --> 00:52:30,920
I am the one who does not allow it.

605
00:52:31,720 --> 00:52:36,040
I won't accept a thief and a murderer's
daughter as a bride before going nuts.

606
00:52:38,040 --> 00:52:40,280
And I never will as long as I live.

607
00:52:41,360 --> 00:52:44,400
As far as I see, they did not feel the need
to ask anyone.

608
00:52:45,360 --> 00:52:46,800
They made their decision.

609
00:52:46,840 --> 00:52:48,480
I do not accept that decision.

610
00:52:48,560 --> 00:52:49,560
Enough!

611
00:53:01,360 --> 00:53:03,280
Neither Mercan nor I are children.

612
00:53:04,280 --> 00:53:05,840
We do not need your permission.

613
00:53:12,440 --> 00:53:15,160
Just because you do not approve...

614
00:53:16,080 --> 00:53:18,520
does not mean I will give up the woman I
love.

615
00:53:32,520 --> 00:53:35,480
We would rather share our happiness.

616
00:53:39,400 --> 00:53:40,440
But if you will not...

617
00:53:41,680 --> 00:53:42,960
do not cast a shadow over it.

618
00:53:50,400 --> 00:53:55,000
Just because you want it does not
mean I will let go of the man I love.

619
00:54:14,000 --> 00:54:15,000
Come on, Nermin.

620
00:54:21,720 --> 00:54:23,640
We will talk in the study in a bit.

621
00:54:41,040 --> 00:54:41,920
I will never allow it.

622
00:54:41,921 --> 00:54:47,880
I will never
allow Mercan to be with that man.

623
00:54:48,440 --> 00:54:50,200
I do not understand why you are so furious.

624
00:54:51,280 --> 00:54:54,440
Would it not be in our
interest if Mercan truly married that man?

625
00:54:56,040 --> 00:54:57,880
All our troubles would end.

626
00:54:58,200 --> 00:54:59,200
How nice.

627
00:54:59,520 --> 00:55:01,200
Do not speak so naively.

628
00:55:01,840 --> 00:55:02,840
Nothing will end.

629
00:55:04,840 --> 00:55:07,600
That man entered our lives to destroy
the Yıldırım family.

630
00:55:08,760 --> 00:55:10,199
That is exactly what he is trying to do.

631
00:55:10,200 --> 00:55:12,240
That is why he is getting close to Mercan.

632
00:55:14,760 --> 00:55:17,600
Great loves are born of great hatreds.

633
00:55:19,400 --> 00:55:21,079
Ateş will soon...

634
00:55:21,080 --> 00:55:23,160
terminate the
contract for his love of Mercan.

635
00:55:24,480 --> 00:55:25,760
Everything will be ours again.

636
00:55:36,240 --> 00:55:37,880
What are you scheming, Ateş?

637
00:55:39,880 --> 00:55:43,040
Why did you visit Eylül’s grave?

638
00:55:45,720 --> 00:55:46,720
Or did you...

639
00:55:58,760 --> 00:55:59,880
Hello, Cevat.

640
00:56:00,920 --> 00:56:01,920
Yes, brother.

641
00:56:02,560 --> 00:56:04,680
There was a boy named Tahir.

642
00:56:05,200 --> 00:56:06,200
From the old days.

643
00:56:07,280 --> 00:56:08,280
Do you remember?

644
00:56:08,520 --> 00:56:10,080
The boy you locked in the basement.

645
00:56:11,840 --> 00:56:13,200
Are you sure he is dead?

646
00:56:14,880 --> 00:56:16,800
What kind of question is that? Of course I
am.

647
00:56:17,840 --> 00:56:21,440
When his bro died, he went berserk,
and while fleeing, a car hit him before me.

648
00:56:22,640 --> 00:56:24,320
There was no sound, no breath left in him.

649
00:56:25,040 --> 00:56:26,160
He lay there lifeless.

650
00:56:28,760 --> 00:56:29,160
All right.

651
00:56:29,480 --> 00:56:30,536
Is something wrong, brother?

652
00:56:30,560 --> 00:56:32,080
We will see whether it is good or bad.

653
00:56:32,600 --> 00:56:33,920
I will call you later.

654
00:56:39,600 --> 00:56:41,080
If Tahir is dead...

655
00:56:41,600 --> 00:56:42,680
Who is Ateş?

656
00:56:44,040 --> 00:56:47,080
Why does he keep visiting Eylül’s grave?

657
00:57:13,280 --> 00:57:14,280
Come here.

658
00:57:26,600 --> 00:57:27,600
They found out.

659
00:57:30,080 --> 00:57:31,080
We are relieved.

660
00:57:33,200 --> 00:57:36,040
But did it seem a bit hard?

661
00:57:36,920 --> 00:57:37,920
Did it?

662
00:57:38,600 --> 00:57:40,000
What happened? I did not notice.

663
00:57:43,480 --> 00:57:44,480
You are so sweet.

664
00:57:54,040 --> 00:57:55,040
Me?

665
00:57:55,520 --> 00:57:57,120
I am very sweet.

666
00:57:57,520 --> 00:57:59,680
Was I not wild, rough, grumpy?

667
00:58:00,800 --> 00:58:02,160
You were, admit it.

668
00:58:03,680 --> 00:58:08,000
But now you suddenly look sweet to me.

669
00:58:09,240 --> 00:58:10,240
I do not know...

670
00:58:12,960 --> 00:58:14,400
They say love is blind.

671
00:58:15,800 --> 00:58:16,800
That must be it.

672
00:58:21,080 --> 00:58:22,680
Did I annoy you too?

673
00:58:23,480 --> 00:58:24,480
Ugh.

674
00:58:24,640 --> 00:58:25,640
Very much so.

675
00:58:26,200 --> 00:58:27,200
Shame on you.

676
00:58:27,520 --> 00:58:28,840
What annoyed you about me?

677
00:58:31,040 --> 00:58:33,200
Just thinking about you irritated me.

678
00:58:41,720 --> 00:58:45,160
You always thought about me?

679
00:58:48,880 --> 00:58:50,280
You never left my mind.

680
00:58:51,560 --> 00:58:53,320
I knew I would lose to you.

681
00:58:54,560 --> 00:58:56,080
I resisted a lot, but it did not work.

682
00:59:02,600 --> 00:59:04,280
I fell in love with you at first sight.

683
00:59:05,840 --> 00:59:07,280
A long time ago.

684
00:59:10,320 --> 00:59:11,760
Really?

685
00:59:12,240 --> 00:59:13,840
Why are you surprised?

686
00:59:19,240 --> 00:59:20,240
Why are you crying?

687
00:59:23,760 --> 00:59:27,200
I am very happy, but also very afraid.

688
00:59:32,160 --> 00:59:33,360
Just be happy.

689
00:59:34,800 --> 00:59:35,800
Do not be afraid.

690
00:59:43,360 --> 00:59:44,480
I love you so much...

691
00:59:49,760 --> 00:59:51,680
I am terrified of losing you.

692
00:59:58,720 --> 01:00:01,000
Anyway, forget all that now.

693
01:00:01,440 --> 01:00:03,000
I upset you too, sorry.

694
01:00:04,920 --> 01:00:06,280
We knew it would be like this.

695
01:00:07,520 --> 01:00:09,840
It will not be easy, it will get harder.

696
01:00:12,280 --> 01:00:18,080
Yes... Facing the truth shook me.

697
01:00:19,560 --> 01:00:20,560
Do not look at me.

698
01:00:23,320 --> 01:00:24,440
I will look at you.

699
01:00:25,760 --> 01:00:26,760
Always.

700
01:00:30,400 --> 01:00:31,480
You keep looking at me.

701
01:00:32,600 --> 01:00:33,880
Always with love.

702
01:00:39,320 --> 01:00:43,880
Do not keep your family waiting.

703
01:00:44,960 --> 01:00:46,200
Let them wait.

704
01:00:50,200 --> 01:00:51,760
I am looking at the woman I love.

705
01:00:53,360 --> 01:00:54,920
Let the whole world wait.

706
01:00:57,640 --> 01:00:59,440
Do not break anyone’s heart.

707
01:01:00,040 --> 01:01:04,119
I do not want anyone hurt because of me.

708
01:01:04,120 --> 01:01:08,040
Even after all they did to you...

709
01:01:09,760 --> 01:01:14,520
I just do
not want anyone to fall out because of me.

710
01:01:15,800 --> 01:01:17,360
I do not want fights.

711
01:01:19,440 --> 01:01:20,440
That is all I want.

712
01:01:20,880 --> 01:01:22,960
Everyone will learn to respect you.

713
01:01:24,360 --> 01:01:26,440
No matter the end, you
are the woman I love.

714
01:01:27,680 --> 01:01:28,680
My wife.

715
01:01:32,840 --> 01:01:34,920
Why did you say no matter the end?

716
01:01:36,640 --> 01:01:38,920
Nothing. Do not dwell on it.

717
01:01:43,440 --> 01:01:44,960
Let us not think of bad things now.

718
01:01:46,040 --> 01:01:47,560
I will be back shortly, all right?

719
01:01:48,480 --> 01:01:49,480
All right.

720
01:02:02,960 --> 01:02:04,520
But it was obvious...

721
01:02:04,960 --> 01:02:06,640
everything happened in plain sight.

722
01:02:07,320 --> 01:02:08,400
And we watched.

723
01:02:08,840 --> 01:02:09,840
Enough, Aslı.

724
01:02:11,560 --> 01:02:12,560
It is not enough, mom.

725
01:02:17,760 --> 01:02:18,920
Not enough.

726
01:02:23,320 --> 01:02:25,800
Mercan will truly be your bride.

727
01:02:26,720 --> 01:02:27,240
Do you not understand?

728
01:02:27,520 --> 01:02:28,880
Calm down, my daughter.

729
01:02:32,160 --> 01:02:33,240
What do you mean calm down?

730
01:02:34,640 --> 01:02:35,640
Calm down.

731
01:02:46,280 --> 01:02:47,920
Mr. Ateş has declared his love.

732
01:02:49,880 --> 01:02:51,360
So, Ateş?

733
01:02:52,400 --> 01:02:54,199
If
Only you had declared your true identity...

734
01:02:54,200 --> 01:02:56,520
and why you are here.

735
01:02:58,400 --> 01:02:59,960
Even told us.

736
01:03:00,280 --> 01:03:01,480
End it all at once.

737
01:03:06,480 --> 01:03:07,920
Get a grip, Aslı.

738
01:03:08,480 --> 01:03:09,560
Watch your words.

739
01:03:11,560 --> 01:03:12,840
I have not strayed from my path.

740
01:03:13,360 --> 01:03:14,360
What will you tell her?

741
01:03:15,400 --> 01:03:16,760
Will you really be able to say it?

742
01:03:17,080 --> 01:03:18,960
Aslı, leave the man alone.

743
01:03:19,880 --> 01:03:21,120
This is not the time for this.

744
01:03:21,480 --> 01:03:23,160
Show some patience and understanding.

745
01:03:23,360 --> 01:03:24,640
What are you saying, Cemal?

746
01:03:25,320 --> 01:03:26,360
What understanding?

747
01:03:27,680 --> 01:03:29,560
Tell this to Ms. Mercan.

748
01:03:30,120 --> 01:03:32,080
Let
us see if you can still hold her hand then.

749
01:03:33,560 --> 01:03:34,960
Or if she will turn away.

750
01:03:35,800 --> 01:03:37,120
Aslı, what is your problem?

751
01:03:38,920 --> 01:03:40,320
This is my issue, not yours.

752
01:03:43,800 --> 01:03:46,720
Do not interfere again.

753
01:03:48,040 --> 01:03:49,360
What about revenge?

754
01:03:54,560 --> 01:03:57,120
Did you give up your plan for the killer’s
daughter?

755
01:03:58,000 --> 01:04:00,320
The plan is the same. Nothing changed.

756
01:04:04,160 --> 01:04:05,280
I will destroy Haydar.

757
01:04:06,840 --> 01:04:10,760
Until I bring about his end, this fire will
not die.

758
01:04:11,680 --> 01:04:15,880
How will you send her father
to prison while holding her in your arms?

759
01:04:16,360 --> 01:04:17,880
Will she not ask you why?

760
01:04:18,000 --> 01:04:19,400
Will she not question what you did?

761
01:04:19,440 --> 01:04:20,440
Mother Müzeyyen.

762
01:04:21,800 --> 01:04:24,320
You on one side, Aslı on the other.

763
01:04:24,920 --> 01:04:27,160
You
are speaking in anger and making mistakes.

764
01:04:28,480 --> 01:04:30,240
He who rises in anger sits in loss.

765
01:04:39,160 --> 01:04:40,160
Yes, Burak?

766
01:04:40,400 --> 01:04:41,400
Hello, brother Ateş?

767
01:04:41,880 --> 01:04:42,880
Speak, Burak.

768
01:04:43,320 --> 01:04:45,160
Brother, I have bad news.

769
01:04:45,600 --> 01:04:46,600
What happened?

770
01:04:47,280 --> 01:04:48,840
Ms. Nermin learned everything.

771
01:04:51,000 --> 01:04:52,800
She knows I am Haydar’s son.

772
01:04:55,840 --> 01:04:57,040
Do not worry.

773
01:04:57,920 --> 01:04:59,280
She was bound to learn eventually.

774
01:05:00,040 --> 01:05:01,840
How did Nermin find out?

775
01:05:03,960 --> 01:05:05,280
I do not know.

776
01:05:06,000 --> 01:05:08,160
She had been following me for a while.

777
01:05:08,480 --> 01:05:09,480
All right.

778
01:05:09,560 --> 01:05:10,560
Wait for my call.

779
01:05:14,120 --> 01:05:15,400
Did Nermin learn about Burak?

780
01:05:21,440 --> 01:05:23,360
Mercan is my red line.

781
01:05:27,760 --> 01:05:30,959
If anyone tries to cross it...

782
01:05:30,960 --> 01:05:33,440
they will face a different Ateş.

783
01:05:40,520 --> 01:05:43,120
No, this will not do.

784
01:05:44,560 --> 01:05:46,360
Ateş has completely lost himself.

785
01:05:46,800 --> 01:05:49,280
He turned against his
own family for that girl.

786
01:05:49,920 --> 01:05:51,280
We need to do something.

787
01:05:51,720 --> 01:05:53,320
Ateş has a special place for me.

788
01:05:54,920 --> 01:05:55,920
Whatever he says goes.

789
01:05:56,440 --> 01:05:58,480
Do not act on your own either.

790
01:06:05,680 --> 01:06:06,680
Mother.

791
01:06:07,720 --> 01:06:10,280
Mother, please do something.

792
01:06:10,360 --> 01:06:11,640
If I do something...

793
01:06:12,360 --> 01:06:14,000
No, no, no, do not, my daughter.

794
01:06:14,320 --> 01:06:15,520
Be quiet, please.

795
01:06:15,800 --> 01:06:17,120
I am not dead yet.

796
01:06:18,760 --> 01:06:20,080
Just wait and see what I will do.

797
01:06:22,760 --> 01:06:23,960
Let things get a little messy.

798
01:06:25,320 --> 01:06:27,360
Ateş will come around.

799
01:07:04,760 --> 01:07:06,920
That is Malik’s phone.

800
01:07:07,960 --> 01:07:08,960
His mother is calling.

801
01:07:11,720 --> 01:07:13,240
Could it be important?

802
01:07:14,160 --> 01:07:15,160
Should I answer?

803
01:07:17,400 --> 01:07:19,080
What would I even say?

804
01:07:19,280 --> 01:07:20,480
What explanation would I give?

805
01:07:30,320 --> 01:07:31,840
MOTHER ARABIC 04

806
01:07:32,080 --> 01:07:34,320
MOTHER ARABIC 05

807
01:07:34,920 --> 01:07:37,000
MOTHER ARABIC 06

808
01:07:37,360 --> 01:07:38,599
MOTHER ARABIC 07

809
01:07:38,600 --> 01:07:41,720
MOTHER ARABIC 08

810
01:07:42,000 --> 01:07:43,000
MOTHER ARABIC 09

811
01:07:43,160 --> 01:07:45,000
MOTHER ARABIC 10

812
01:07:48,600 --> 01:07:49,840
MOTHER ARABIC 11

813
01:07:50,080 --> 01:07:51,080
MOTHER ARABIC 12

814
01:07:51,240 --> 01:07:52,680
MOTHER ARABIC 13

815
01:07:56,640 --> 01:07:58,840
Do not give false hope, Çiçek.

816
01:07:59,880 --> 01:08:01,640
Turn back while you still can.

817
01:08:33,160 --> 01:08:34,160
What happened?

818
01:08:35,280 --> 01:08:36,280
Why did you call me?

819
01:08:40,200 --> 01:08:42,200
Nezir, so much has happened.

820
01:08:45,200 --> 01:08:49,160
Mercan and Ateş appeared
hand in hand and declared their love.

821
01:08:51,880 --> 01:08:52,880
What?

822
01:08:53,920 --> 01:08:54,920
What are you saying?

823
01:08:59,960 --> 01:09:03,640
I think you should forget Mercan now.

824
01:09:05,680 --> 01:09:07,360
What are you talking about?

825
01:09:07,600 --> 01:09:10,640
This is what I feared.

826
01:09:26,880 --> 01:09:27,880
I will not forget.

827
01:09:28,560 --> 01:09:30,000
I will not forget, Ms. Nermin.

828
01:09:32,520 --> 01:09:34,120
She is unaware of everything right now.

829
01:09:35,120 --> 01:09:36,280
I will kill Ateş.

830
01:09:37,080 --> 01:09:38,080
I will kill him.

831
01:09:39,680 --> 01:09:41,120
Nermin, leave us alone for a bit.

832
01:09:41,680 --> 01:09:42,840
We need to talk privately.

833
01:09:53,120 --> 01:09:54,160
Calm down first.

834
01:09:54,720 --> 01:09:56,440
I cannot calm down, Haydar.

835
01:09:57,120 --> 01:09:58,120
Do you understand?

836
01:09:59,520 --> 01:10:00,640
You should have stopped it.

837
01:10:01,160 --> 01:10:02,040
You should have stopped it.

838
01:10:02,120 --> 01:10:03,320
I cannot lose Mercan.

839
01:10:04,240 --> 01:10:05,360
What is done is done, Nezir.

840
01:10:05,880 --> 01:10:08,840
Now my concern is how to get rid of Ateş.

841
01:10:09,200 --> 01:10:10,800
I reached important information.

842
01:10:12,000 --> 01:10:12,720
Fatih.

843
01:10:12,920 --> 01:10:13,920
Ateş’s man.

844
01:10:14,440 --> 01:10:17,200
Before fleeing, he said
Ateş had a dead brother.

845
01:10:17,640 --> 01:10:19,399
I checked the records.
There is no such thing.

846
01:10:19,400 --> 01:10:20,400
He has no brother.

847
01:10:20,640 --> 01:10:21,760
He was stammering.

848
01:10:22,480 --> 01:10:23,480
What does this mean?

849
01:10:23,920 --> 01:10:27,240
It means there may be no one called Ateş.

850
01:10:29,720 --> 01:10:32,080
We do not even know who this man is.

851
01:10:41,680 --> 01:10:44,560
And this man is taking my Mercan.

852
01:10:46,160 --> 01:10:48,640
I will make you pay for this.

853
01:10:50,120 --> 01:10:51,320
I will kill you.

854
01:11:05,560 --> 01:11:06,680
Welcome, my child.

855
01:11:06,840 --> 01:11:07,920
Thank you, Ms. Müzeyyen.

856
01:11:08,200 --> 01:11:09,200
Welcome.

857
01:11:10,000 --> 01:11:10,440
Sit down.

858
01:11:10,960 --> 01:11:11,960
Thank you.

859
01:11:16,360 --> 01:11:18,120
Is Ateş not here?

860
01:11:20,080 --> 01:11:21,080
He will come.

861
01:11:27,000 --> 01:11:28,640
The time has come for certain things.

862
01:11:28,800 --> 01:11:30,800
I called you to talk about them.

863
01:11:35,480 --> 01:11:37,640
Ateş told me to wait for his word.

864
01:11:39,160 --> 01:11:40,400
I know, my boy.

865
01:11:40,600 --> 01:11:41,600
I know everything.

866
01:11:45,600 --> 01:11:48,160
And it is time to speak.

867
01:12:16,360 --> 01:12:18,120
I wondered how you were.

868
01:12:19,120 --> 01:12:21,120
Come here.

869
01:12:22,040 --> 01:12:23,480
I need to talk.

870
01:12:26,520 --> 01:12:27,520
I will come right away.

871
01:12:49,640 --> 01:12:50,640
How was it?

872
01:12:52,000 --> 01:12:53,640
Let us not talk about this now.

873
01:12:54,760 --> 01:12:55,760
Come, hold me.

874
01:12:57,680 --> 01:12:58,680
Tight.

875
01:13:09,880 --> 01:13:11,880
As long as you are with me...

876
01:13:12,800 --> 01:13:13,800
nothing else matters.

877
01:13:17,240 --> 01:13:20,320
I accept everything with you.

878
01:13:22,000 --> 01:13:23,880
I am strong with you.

879
01:13:24,880 --> 01:13:26,160
I believe in our love.

880
01:13:26,680 --> 01:13:27,680
I believe in you.

881
01:13:29,440 --> 01:13:30,600
No one can hurt us.

882
01:13:31,600 --> 01:13:32,600
Except ourselves.

883
01:13:33,000 --> 01:13:34,000
I know.

884
01:13:34,280 --> 01:13:35,280
I have strength.

885
01:13:36,000 --> 01:13:37,640
I would stand against the whole world.

886
01:13:38,560 --> 01:13:39,760
As long as we fight together.

887
01:13:40,720 --> 01:13:43,400
You are the strongest,
bravest woman I know.

888
01:13:44,760 --> 01:13:45,760
And stubborn.

889
01:13:47,320 --> 01:13:48,320
A little.

890
01:13:49,400 --> 01:13:50,760
I am glad you are.

891
01:13:54,400 --> 01:13:56,400
Our strength will keep us together again.

892
01:13:58,480 --> 01:14:00,080
We have been through very hard times.

893
01:14:00,200 --> 01:14:01,600
We overcame great ordeals.

894
01:14:03,280 --> 01:14:06,680
Yet nothing defeated our love.

895
01:14:07,480 --> 01:14:08,760
Look, we are here.

896
01:14:09,760 --> 01:14:10,760
Side by side.

897
01:14:13,480 --> 01:14:16,800
I worried you earlier, I know.

898
01:14:18,360 --> 01:14:20,080
Yes, I am afraid.

899
01:14:20,560 --> 01:14:21,760
Very afraid.

900
01:14:23,360 --> 01:14:24,720
But I know.

901
01:14:27,040 --> 01:14:29,640
Our love will grow stronger with
every test.

902
01:14:32,840 --> 01:14:34,640
There are things I have not told you.

903
01:14:35,560 --> 01:14:38,160
Our biggest test
will be when I tell you the truth.

904
01:14:45,600 --> 01:14:47,080
How will I tell you the truth?

905
01:14:47,720 --> 01:14:49,120
What if you hate me?

906
01:14:49,680 --> 01:14:50,920
What if you give up on us?

907
01:14:51,600 --> 01:14:52,600
I could not bear it.

908
01:14:53,680 --> 01:14:55,720
I am terrified of losing you.

909
01:15:00,680 --> 01:15:02,120
Are you going to say something?

910
01:15:04,560 --> 01:15:06,040
I have to.

911
01:15:07,000 --> 01:15:08,000
But how?

912
01:15:11,720 --> 01:15:15,200
You look like you want to say something.

913
01:15:16,280 --> 01:15:19,840
I thought you were about to say something.

914
01:15:21,840 --> 01:15:22,920
You guessed right.

915
01:15:23,680 --> 01:15:24,760
What were you going to say?

916
01:15:30,680 --> 01:15:33,360
Shall we leave here for a while, Ateş?

917
01:15:37,800 --> 01:15:40,200
Let us go far away from
everyone and everything.

918
01:16:39,800 --> 01:16:44,400
Would it not be nice to
step away from all this chaos for a while?

919
01:16:46,360 --> 01:16:47,360
It would.

920
01:16:49,040 --> 01:16:54,200
Look, I am not afraid of what
will happen, or of our families’ reactions.

921
01:16:55,040 --> 01:16:56,160
I know you are not afraid.

922
01:16:57,360 --> 01:17:01,000
I am aware this is not
something we can completely escape anyway.

923
01:17:02,680 --> 01:17:05,200
I
Just wanted to steal a little time for us.

924
01:17:06,640 --> 01:17:07,800
So we could gather strength.

925
01:17:09,520 --> 01:17:11,760
So we could let our love grow.

926
01:17:15,160 --> 01:17:16,640
Mercan, I do not know.

927
01:17:17,680 --> 01:17:20,920
Do
You not want to go? You can tell me openly.

928
01:17:21,840 --> 01:17:23,000
It is not like that.

929
01:17:23,520 --> 01:17:25,240
Ateş, is something wrong?

930
01:17:26,120 --> 01:17:28,360
Ateş, is something wrong?

931
01:17:32,640 --> 01:17:37,159
If you heard what is inside me,
you would either hold me and cry with me...

932
01:17:37,160 --> 01:17:40,240
or you would hate me and walk
away. There is no middle ground.

933
01:17:42,160 --> 01:17:45,600
Ateş, do not build new walls between us.

934
01:17:46,480 --> 01:17:47,480
Never.

935
01:17:49,160 --> 01:17:50,920
I
Would never be the one to build that wall.

936
01:17:52,480 --> 01:17:53,680
What do you mean?

937
01:17:57,040 --> 01:17:58,800
You are my everything.

938
01:17:59,240 --> 01:18:02,400
How could I build walls when I am you?

939
01:18:06,120 --> 01:18:08,600
You have a trouble you
cannot say. It is obvious.

940
01:18:12,880 --> 01:18:16,760
You know,
we never broke down the old things easily.

941
01:18:17,920 --> 01:18:19,640
But together we are strong.

942
01:18:21,040 --> 01:18:22,360
No one can tear us down.

943
01:18:24,160 --> 01:18:25,160
Come on, tell me.

944
01:18:33,840 --> 01:18:35,520
Mercan, this might not be the right time.

945
01:18:36,840 --> 01:18:38,359
But we need to talk...

946
01:18:38,360 --> 01:18:39,640
How did you learn this?

947
01:18:40,080 --> 01:18:42,200
Well, I learned it somehow.

948
01:18:42,480 --> 01:18:43,480
What is going on?

949
01:18:43,880 --> 01:18:45,360
Do I owe you an explanation?

950
01:18:47,480 --> 01:18:49,840
How did you learn Burak is Haydar’s son?

951
01:18:50,720 --> 01:18:52,920
Well, I learned it somehow.

952
01:18:53,600 --> 01:18:55,680
Your disgraces always
come out one way or another.

953
01:18:57,360 --> 01:18:59,240
Stay away from my family.

954
01:19:00,120 --> 01:19:01,120
What family exactly?

955
01:19:03,760 --> 01:19:05,160
You call this a family?

956
01:19:06,320 --> 01:19:07,320
Pathetic.

957
01:19:10,440 --> 01:19:11,440
What is going on?

958
01:19:11,960 --> 01:19:13,560
Why are you all shouting again?

959
01:19:14,160 --> 01:19:15,320
Everything is in chaos again.

960
01:19:15,640 --> 01:19:19,400
I thought I would introduce you to
your son, but Mrs. Nermin panicked a bit.

961
01:19:20,120 --> 01:19:21,320
What nonsense are you talking?

962
01:19:23,360 --> 01:19:25,800
What son are
you talking about? A new madness every day.

963
01:19:26,000 --> 01:19:27,000
Enough already.

964
01:19:31,240 --> 01:19:32,920
What is happening, what is all this noise?

965
01:19:33,160 --> 01:19:35,320
Mrs.
Müzeyyen is trying to stir things up again.

966
01:19:37,480 --> 01:19:39,640
Apparently she staged a new show.

967
01:19:39,800 --> 01:19:41,560
Burak is my
son, she says. Let us all watch.

968
01:19:42,720 --> 01:19:43,720
What?

969
01:20:07,960 --> 01:20:15,960
(rhubarb)

970
01:20:27,840 --> 01:20:31,440
Treachery has become a habit with you.
If you do not believe me, ask your wife.

971
01:20:32,760 --> 01:20:40,760
(rhubarb)

972
01:20:44,680 --> 01:20:45,680
It is true.

973
01:20:46,360 --> 01:20:47,840
Speak the truth to my mother.

974
01:21:09,800 --> 01:21:11,600
I am Haydar Yıldırım’s son.

975
01:22:04,040 --> 01:22:05,040
Oh Çiçek.

976
01:22:05,120 --> 01:22:08,320
Çiçek, stop.
For God’s sake, stop. Please listen to me.

977
01:22:09,800 --> 01:22:12,280
Çiçek, stop. Listen to me. For God’s sake.

978
01:22:12,520 --> 01:22:14,600
Look, what you just heard means nothing.

979
01:22:14,640 --> 01:22:16,920
It changes nothing. I love you so much.

980
01:22:17,080 --> 01:22:18,240
Do not waste your breath.

981
01:22:19,400 --> 01:22:21,000
You are the Prince of Egypt, after all.

982
01:22:22,160 --> 01:22:23,160
Go sit on your throne.

983
01:22:24,160 --> 01:22:26,280
Why are you chasing a servant like me?

984
01:22:27,040 --> 01:22:29,480
You had your fun. It is over. That is it.

985
01:22:30,000 --> 01:22:33,080
What do you mean
you had your fun, Çiçek? What do you mean?

986
01:22:33,360 --> 01:22:35,320
Could
there ever be such a thing, for God’s sake?

987
01:22:35,600 --> 01:22:39,200
You
are my princess. You already own my heart.

988
01:22:40,200 --> 01:22:42,600
The topic of your family came up
many times.

989
01:22:43,160 --> 01:22:45,160
You never told the truth.

990
01:22:45,520 --> 01:22:47,440
You always dodged it, brushed it off.

991
01:22:48,080 --> 01:22:49,600
What did you think, Malik?

992
01:22:50,160 --> 01:22:52,720
Did you think I would
cling to you once I learned you were rich?

993
01:22:53,080 --> 01:22:54,920
Did you think I would chase your money?

994
01:22:55,040 --> 01:22:56,616
Do not do this. You are being unfair to me.

995
01:22:56,640 --> 01:22:58,600
Would
I ever think something like that about you?

996
01:22:58,680 --> 01:23:01,000
Believe me, I do
not care what you think anymore.

997
01:23:01,400 --> 01:23:02,719
Çiçek, just...

998
01:23:02,720 --> 01:23:06,680
Listen to me. For God’s sake, listen.

999
01:23:08,960 --> 01:23:10,080
What is this stubbornness?

1000
01:23:11,760 --> 01:23:14,280
If only you knew the truth.

1001
01:23:15,920 --> 01:23:17,600
Oh my God, what have you done to me, Mom?!

1002
01:23:18,440 --> 01:23:20,280
If you could see what you did to me!!

1003
01:23:25,720 --> 01:23:27,560
Have you all gone mad?

1004
01:23:28,000 --> 01:23:32,160
This man is either lying or he is a con
artist playing along with this woman’s games.

1005
01:23:37,200 --> 01:23:40,080
Why would I need to scheme, Mr. Haydar?

1006
01:23:40,840 --> 01:23:43,360
You are already dancing to your own tune.

1007
01:23:45,320 --> 01:23:46,840
The outcome is right there.

1008
01:23:47,280 --> 01:23:49,080
Watch it, woman. You are crossing the line.

1009
01:23:49,440 --> 01:23:50,440
Enough.

1010
01:23:52,560 --> 01:23:54,080
Stop it. Be quiet now.

1011
01:24:04,920 --> 01:24:05,720
Burak...

1012
01:24:05,721 --> 01:24:06,960
tell me the truth.

1013
01:24:08,280 --> 01:24:09,280
Please.

1014
01:24:10,960 --> 01:24:12,720
Believe me, I am telling you the truth.

1015
01:24:20,480 --> 01:24:22,360
But if you do not believe me...

1016
01:24:23,160 --> 01:24:25,400
You can look at the DNA report.

1017
01:24:49,840 --> 01:24:51,200
I was forced to do it.

1018
01:24:59,840 --> 01:25:01,360
I took a strand of hair from him.

1019
01:25:07,480 --> 01:25:12,640
If you still do not believe me, I can have
another DNA test done.

1020
01:25:26,480 --> 01:25:27,560
He is telling the truth.

1021
01:25:45,240 --> 01:25:46,160
You...

1022
01:25:46,161 --> 01:25:48,960
Did you lie to us again, dad?

1023
01:25:53,520 --> 01:25:55,840
Did you do things behind our backs again?

1024
01:25:56,640 --> 01:25:58,400
Will I never be able to trust you?

1025
01:26:02,240 --> 01:26:03,799
No one has the courage
to take responsibility...

1026
01:26:03,800 --> 01:26:05,720
for what they have done.

1027
01:26:16,960 --> 01:26:19,400
No one has the courage to be honest either.

1028
01:26:22,480 --> 01:26:23,600
Shame on you.

1029
01:26:38,000 --> 01:26:39,760
All right, calm down please.

1030
01:26:48,960 --> 01:26:51,080
You go to the study.

1031
01:27:01,840 --> 01:27:04,520
I wish the only thing I felt was shame.

1032
01:27:05,240 --> 01:27:08,600
But you caused me the
deepest disappointment.

1033
01:27:11,040 --> 01:27:12,560
I will never forgive you.

1034
01:27:22,520 --> 01:27:23,520
Never.

1035
01:27:32,880 --> 01:27:35,960
All right, my dear. I understand. See you.

1036
01:27:48,760 --> 01:27:51,680
Do not go inside for nothing. Everything is
a mess.

1037
01:27:54,680 --> 01:27:55,680
Yours.

1038
01:27:56,640 --> 01:27:59,480
He put on another show.
Documents, statements, all of it.

1039
01:28:01,440 --> 01:28:02,720
Do you know who Burak is?

1040
01:28:03,760 --> 01:28:06,760
Stop saying yours. I just learned myself.

1041
01:28:07,960 --> 01:28:11,280
So what does this mean, Demet? You
should listen to your brother, right?

1042
01:28:12,080 --> 01:28:14,200
When I tell you something, it means I know
something.

1043
01:28:15,960 --> 01:28:17,920
You saw how unreliable Burak is.

1044
01:28:20,720 --> 01:28:23,560
Yes, I admit it. He kept a secret.

1045
01:28:26,040 --> 01:28:29,360
But that does not
change the fact he is a good person.

1046
01:28:30,200 --> 01:28:31,200
He is a victim too.

1047
01:28:31,480 --> 01:28:35,080
Bravo to you for
finding something to defend that scoundrel.

1048
01:28:36,000 --> 01:28:37,656
All right, enough. Walk ahead. We will talk
at home.

1049
01:28:37,680 --> 01:28:40,520
You go.
I will check on Mercan. I will come later.

1050
01:28:43,840 --> 01:28:47,440
All right.
I should talk too, but now is not the time.

1051
01:28:48,200 --> 01:28:49,840
There is one thing I do not understand.

1052
01:28:50,960 --> 01:28:53,160
Burak’s connection to the Karahans...

1053
01:28:56,840 --> 01:28:59,440
I would not be surprised
if Ateş was behind this too.

1054
01:29:00,280 --> 01:29:01,360
Come on, brother.

1055
01:29:13,960 --> 01:29:16,560
Son, stop. My head is spinning.

1056
01:29:23,480 --> 01:29:26,720
What a day.
A storm, an apocalypse, everything at once.

1057
01:29:28,440 --> 01:29:32,519
I sensed something was off with Malik from
the start...

1058
01:29:32,520 --> 01:29:35,759
when he suddenly handed over all
that money.

1059
01:29:35,760 --> 01:29:37,640
That is when I got suspicious.

1060
01:29:38,800 --> 01:29:39,960
He even fooled me.

1061
01:29:44,720 --> 01:29:48,840
I cared too much. Otherwise
I would have noticed.

1062
01:29:52,360 --> 01:29:56,320
Who knows
how many lies he told and made us believe.

1063
01:29:57,440 --> 01:29:59,400
A liar is always a liar.

1064
01:29:59,960 --> 01:30:01,360
Yes, we know that from you.

1065
01:30:12,080 --> 01:30:14,360
Do not cry, my girl. Do not upset yourself.

1066
01:30:14,800 --> 01:30:17,080
At least we found out early.

1067
01:30:21,760 --> 01:30:24,840
Early? What early?

1068
01:30:25,680 --> 01:30:27,440
From now on, you will do as I say.

1069
01:30:28,000 --> 01:30:31,480
You trust people too easily. You open your
heart to everyone.

1070
01:30:31,680 --> 01:30:32,360
That is not true.

1071
01:30:32,680 --> 01:30:36,000
Brother, please stop. I beg you.

1072
01:30:55,120 --> 01:30:57,520
Do not cry, my flower.

1073
01:31:01,760 --> 01:31:03,560
There is good in every hardship.

1074
01:31:07,280 --> 01:31:11,240
Trouble comes to everyone in this life.

1075
01:31:11,880 --> 01:31:14,480
Life is not always roses.

1076
01:31:16,080 --> 01:31:17,680
You learn lessons from some things.

1077
01:31:19,320 --> 01:31:23,640
You learned your lesson. Now you move on.

1078
01:31:24,560 --> 01:31:26,640
Do not upset yourself. Come on, mom. Do not
cry.

1079
01:31:29,800 --> 01:31:33,480
If you knew earlier, why didn't you say
anything? We could have taken precautions.

1080
01:31:34,840 --> 01:31:37,360
You should have taken
that precaution twenty years ago, Haydar.

1081
01:31:38,160 --> 01:31:40,720
Nermin, is this the time for jabs?

1082
01:31:41,920 --> 01:31:46,160
I just learned myself.
I cannot keep up with your filth.

1083
01:31:48,600 --> 01:31:51,240
First I learned he was Nurgül’s son.

1084
01:31:53,760 --> 01:31:54,760
Nurgül?

1085
01:31:57,080 --> 01:31:58,240
What?

1086
01:31:59,680 --> 01:32:01,000
You seem surprised, Haydar.

1087
01:32:03,960 --> 01:32:05,400
Are there others too, Haydar?

1088
01:32:06,560 --> 01:32:10,640
Damn you. Damn you, Insallah.

1089
01:32:10,760 --> 01:32:11,760
Enough.

1090
01:32:13,800 --> 01:32:14,800
All right.

1091
01:32:17,560 --> 01:32:20,880
A new incident, a new lie every time.

1092
01:32:25,400 --> 01:32:26,840
Dad, you were my hero.

1093
01:32:28,400 --> 01:32:30,160
How could you betray us?

1094
01:32:34,760 --> 01:32:35,760
And you?

1095
01:32:36,640 --> 01:32:39,800
How could you stay silent knowing all this?
Why did you keep quiet?

1096
01:32:43,560 --> 01:32:47,240
What else do I not know? Tell me.

1097
01:32:47,440 --> 01:32:50,240
Tell me, because I am exhausted from being
hurt.

1098
01:32:51,480 --> 01:32:54,120
My daughter, I
am not in a state to mend hearts right now.

1099
01:32:58,000 --> 01:32:59,200
My own troubles are enough.

1100
01:32:59,800 --> 01:33:01,680
I need to process this first.

1101
01:33:02,760 --> 01:33:04,200
Of course you made a mess.

1102
01:33:05,280 --> 01:33:06,800
Sit and try to digest it.

1103
01:33:13,040 --> 01:33:15,080
I am disgraced again because of you.

1104
01:33:16,560 --> 01:33:17,640
It is always you, right?

1105
01:33:20,600 --> 01:33:22,320
Oh, you are the ones disgraced.

1106
01:33:24,080 --> 01:33:27,320
What does Mercan feel?
What does that boy feel? No one cares.

1107
01:34:13,640 --> 01:34:15,840
Can we talk a bit, Burak?

1108
01:34:22,120 --> 01:34:23,840
Sit down.

1109
01:34:27,800 --> 01:34:29,160
Why did you not tell me?

1110
01:34:34,840 --> 01:34:38,400
I am so sorry. I could not.

1111
01:34:42,440 --> 01:34:44,440
I learned when I was a child.

1112
01:34:46,760 --> 01:34:47,760
Then...

1113
01:34:47,761 --> 01:34:51,080
My mother made me swear not to go.

1114
01:34:53,920 --> 01:34:55,760
I always watched you from afar.

1115
01:35:01,960 --> 01:35:03,359
Sometimes...

1116
01:35:03,360 --> 01:35:05,960
I saw you in tabloid news.

1117
01:35:08,200 --> 01:35:10,200
You were both real and unreal.

1118
01:35:15,760 --> 01:35:17,959
After my mother died...

1119
01:35:17,960 --> 01:35:20,960
I broke my oath and joined the company.

1120
01:35:26,920 --> 01:35:28,320
Because...

1121
01:35:31,040 --> 01:35:33,559
even from afar...

1122
01:35:33,560 --> 01:35:37,480
I wanted to know my father and siblings.

1123
01:35:39,000 --> 01:35:40,960
I wanted to be with my family.

1124
01:35:46,680 --> 01:35:48,920
Then things came to this point.

1125
01:35:56,600 --> 01:35:59,840
I am truly sorry for disturbing your peace,
Mercan.

1126
01:36:06,080 --> 01:36:07,240
I wish I had never been born.

1127
01:36:14,280 --> 01:36:16,200
You did nothing wrong.

1128
01:36:19,160 --> 01:36:20,839
We both...

1129
01:36:20,840 --> 01:36:24,080
are paying for our parents’ sins.

1130
01:36:27,480 --> 01:36:28,840
It is not easy for either of us.

1131
01:36:35,760 --> 01:36:39,280
But I need some time.

1132
01:36:40,720 --> 01:36:41,720
Please understand me.

1133
01:36:46,520 --> 01:36:48,080
I am very sorry for this.

1134
01:37:05,040 --> 01:37:07,680
I cannot bear seeing Mercan sad.

1135
01:37:09,120 --> 01:37:10,760
She does not deserve this.

1136
01:37:11,720 --> 01:37:12,720
Truly.

1137
01:37:14,440 --> 01:37:15,520
She is not like her family.

1138
01:37:19,360 --> 01:37:21,120
Her biggest trial is her family.

1139
01:37:22,520 --> 01:37:24,520
And she passed this trial many times.

1140
01:37:29,840 --> 01:37:31,600
Yet she carries all the pain again.

1141
01:37:39,360 --> 01:37:40,800
Mercan said let us go.

1142
01:37:42,920 --> 01:37:44,120
She wants to leave this place.

1143
01:37:46,760 --> 01:37:47,800
Is she wrong, brother?

1144
01:37:49,000 --> 01:37:51,360
Who would
want to stay in this hell, for God’s sake?

1145
01:37:52,920 --> 01:37:54,240
I think you should listen to her.

1146
01:37:54,920 --> 01:37:57,120
Get away from here. Clear your heads for a
while.

1147
01:38:00,840 --> 01:38:02,160
How are we supposed to go, Cemal?

1148
01:38:02,560 --> 01:38:04,320
This is not
the time to run, but to face it.

1149
01:38:08,080 --> 01:38:11,080
I do not want to deceive her anymore.

1150
01:38:13,840 --> 01:38:15,880
I cannot go on without telling the truth.

1151
01:38:20,600 --> 01:38:22,040
I have to do this today.

1152
01:38:25,240 --> 01:38:27,360
Ateş, are you sure?

1153
01:38:28,040 --> 01:38:29,560
You mean you will tell her everything?

1154
01:38:30,600 --> 01:38:32,720
If you ask me, it is not the right time.

1155
01:38:36,240 --> 01:38:38,440
There is no right or wrong time anymore.

1156
01:38:59,840 --> 01:39:02,440
Why did you
attempt this without telling me?

1157
01:39:03,760 --> 01:39:07,400
Well, Mr. Ateş,
Mrs. Müzeyyen called. She told me to come.

1158
01:39:07,920 --> 01:39:10,320
I thought you knew.

1159
01:39:17,320 --> 01:39:18,840
All right, Burak, you leave.

1160
01:39:27,520 --> 01:39:30,840
I told you to stop. I
told you not to do anything without me.

1161
01:39:31,600 --> 01:39:33,440
Why do you never listen to me?

1162
01:39:34,400 --> 01:39:37,559
Did we not want Burak to
come out and disrupt the Yıldırıms’ peace?

1163
01:39:37,560 --> 01:39:39,640
Well, it is disrupted now. What more?

1164
01:39:43,960 --> 01:39:50,640
Yes. While you were dealing with your
personal matters, we continued our plan.

1165
01:39:54,400 --> 01:39:56,720
No matter what, we should have informed
Ateş.

1166
01:39:57,680 --> 01:40:02,000
We did not come here for amusement, son. We
came to make up for the pain of the past.

1167
01:40:05,800 --> 01:40:10,160
We came to hurt those who hurt us and heal
our wounds.

1168
01:40:15,160 --> 01:40:21,600
But you left us, Ateş.

1169
01:40:50,880 --> 01:40:51,880
Let that hand be cut off.

1170
01:42:05,440 --> 01:42:09,120
Will this
ever end in this mansion? Chaos everywhere.

1171
01:42:11,480 --> 01:42:12,480
What happened?

1172
01:42:15,280 --> 01:42:18,600
I see gossip caught your
attention, Ms. Çiçek.

1173
01:42:18,840 --> 01:42:19,840
No, mom.

1174
01:42:20,880 --> 01:42:24,760
You know that boy named
Burak at the company?

1175
01:42:25,160 --> 01:42:25,800
Yes.

1176
01:42:25,801 --> 01:42:30,520
Well, it turns out
he is Mr. Haydar’s son from another woman.

1177
01:42:30,760 --> 01:42:33,840
What? Are you serious, mom?

1178
01:42:34,520 --> 01:42:37,680
No, my girl. I made it up as a joke.

1179
01:42:37,920 --> 01:42:40,680
Of course I am serious.
All hell broke loose at the mansion.

1180
01:42:42,040 --> 01:42:43,040
Oh dear.

1181
01:42:43,680 --> 01:42:46,920
I cannot even say I am surprised.

1182
01:42:47,560 --> 01:42:49,960
It was something to expect from Mr. Haydar.

1183
01:42:50,360 --> 01:42:52,440
True. You are right.

1184
01:42:53,200 --> 01:42:55,640
A person is either straight or crooked.

1185
01:42:56,280 --> 01:42:58,480
Mr. Haydar is crooked. Always was.

1186
01:43:00,160 --> 01:43:02,200
Poor Murat suffered the most.

1187
01:43:02,520 --> 01:43:04,560
He never knew how to treat that boy.

1188
01:43:04,880 --> 01:43:07,079
One moment kind, the next cruel.

1189
01:43:07,080 --> 01:43:09,280
Back and forth.

1190
01:43:12,040 --> 01:43:15,600
Thank God Burak grew up far away Insallah.

1191
01:43:16,080 --> 01:43:18,520
He never saw his father’s bad habits.

1192
01:43:19,800 --> 01:43:23,200
If Murat had been his real son...

1193
01:43:23,800 --> 01:43:25,360
He might have treated him better too.

1194
01:43:25,720 --> 01:43:27,640
What? I did not hear you.

1195
01:43:28,240 --> 01:43:29,880
I said fate, my girl. Fate.

1196
01:43:30,200 --> 01:43:32,840
Sometimes what you think is good turns out
bad.

1197
01:43:33,240 --> 01:43:34,880
And what you think is bad turns out good.

1198
01:43:36,280 --> 01:43:37,280
Really?

1199
01:43:38,040 --> 01:43:39,040
Yes.

1200
01:43:40,080 --> 01:43:42,480
So is my breakup with Malik good?

1201
01:43:44,120 --> 01:43:45,560
But it hurts so much, mom.

1202
01:44:11,880 --> 01:44:13,560
I am glad you brought me here.

1203
01:44:14,320 --> 01:44:15,920
I am glad we left the mansion.

1204
01:44:17,160 --> 01:44:21,640
When you pulled me out of the room, I felt
like I had no other choice.

1205
01:44:22,840 --> 01:44:24,280
You said let us do something.

1206
01:44:26,000 --> 01:44:27,480
I really ran away, did I not?

1207
01:44:28,520 --> 01:44:29,520
You did.

1208
01:44:29,840 --> 01:44:31,680
If you had not, I would have.

1209
01:44:35,280 --> 01:44:37,200
I could not stay, Ateş.

1210
01:44:37,240 --> 01:44:38,680
I could not take it anymore.

1211
01:44:40,560 --> 01:44:43,160
Everything came down on me.

1212
01:44:46,400 --> 01:44:48,080
I had a sibling all this time.

1213
01:44:49,320 --> 01:44:50,920
Living apart from us.

1214
01:44:56,480 --> 01:44:58,280
How did Mrs. Müzeyyen hear about this?

1215
01:44:59,080 --> 01:45:04,280
Look, since we are far from
the mansion now, stop thinking about it.

1216
01:45:05,760 --> 01:45:06,920
I cannot help it.

1217
01:45:08,200 --> 01:45:10,760
Something about my father keeps coming out.

1218
01:45:12,200 --> 01:45:15,080
I never truly knew the
people I called family.

1219
01:45:18,280 --> 01:45:20,000
I cannot even defend them.

1220
01:45:21,520 --> 01:45:23,120
That place was my family, my everything.

1221
01:45:24,000 --> 01:45:25,840
I did everything for them.

1222
01:45:31,200 --> 01:45:35,920
One should have parents to rely on.

1223
01:45:36,320 --> 01:45:37,440
Whose door one can knock on.

1224
01:45:39,200 --> 01:45:41,480
I realized I have no one.

1225
01:45:49,000 --> 01:45:50,000
Do not say that.

1226
01:45:57,200 --> 01:45:58,200
I am here.

1227
01:46:00,480 --> 01:46:01,480
You are not alone.

1228
01:46:04,680 --> 01:46:05,680
I know.

1229
01:46:06,680 --> 01:46:07,680
I am glad you are here.

1230
01:46:10,880 --> 01:46:13,400
You make me feel so good.

1231
01:46:15,520 --> 01:46:16,520
You too.

1232
01:46:34,560 --> 01:46:37,040
As
Long as you are here, I accept everything.

1233
01:46:38,920 --> 01:46:41,240
Laughter and tears alike.

1234
01:46:50,400 --> 01:46:51,520
Always smile.

1235
01:46:52,400 --> 01:46:53,400
My beautiful one.

1236
01:46:57,760 --> 01:46:58,920
Always smile.

1237
01:47:11,320 --> 01:47:13,440
It was supposed to be a beautiful day.

1238
01:47:14,840 --> 01:47:16,760
It still can be.

1239
01:47:18,720 --> 01:47:19,920
Do you have something in mind?

1240
01:47:23,360 --> 01:47:24,400
Come with me.

1241
01:47:41,200 --> 01:47:42,680
Exactly. Yes. Exactly.

1242
01:47:42,800 --> 01:47:45,120
Yes, you are right. Let us do that too.

1243
01:47:45,440 --> 01:47:47,280
Exactly. All right.

1244
01:47:47,360 --> 01:47:48,440
See you.

1245
01:47:49,800 --> 01:47:51,200
I am losing my mind.

1246
01:47:51,760 --> 01:47:52,760
What is all this?

1247
01:47:54,000 --> 01:47:55,439
Hello? Hello?

1248
01:47:55,440 --> 01:47:57,440
Yes, Mr. Ersin.

1249
01:47:57,840 --> 01:47:59,520
Sorry, Ms. Esin.

1250
01:47:59,680 --> 01:48:01,000
Sorry, sorry. My apologies.

1251
01:48:01,200 --> 01:48:02,200
See you at three.

1252
01:48:02,480 --> 01:48:04,560
Right, right. Not three, five.

1253
01:48:05,960 --> 01:48:07,840
I really misunderstood.

1254
01:48:07,880 --> 01:48:09,600
At five. All right.

1255
01:48:10,000 --> 01:48:11,000
See you.

1256
01:48:13,760 --> 01:48:15,480
I am all mixed up now.

1257
01:48:17,280 --> 01:48:20,280
Ms. Zahide, you see how much I work, right?

1258
01:48:20,320 --> 01:48:22,320
I am carrying the company on my shoulders.

1259
01:48:23,240 --> 01:48:24,559
Is there a holiday or something?

1260
01:48:24,560 --> 01:48:27,680
Everyone
disappeared. There is no one here to work.

1261
01:48:28,040 --> 01:48:33,160
By the way, tell Mr. Ateş to
pay my salary and overtime tenfold today.

1262
01:48:35,480 --> 01:48:37,040
Here you go, Mr. Yaşar.

1263
01:48:37,200 --> 01:48:38,640
These are the last files.

1264
01:48:38,840 --> 01:48:41,560
Should I convey your last words to
Mr. Ateş?

1265
01:48:41,840 --> 01:48:42,840
Yes, do.

1266
01:48:47,360 --> 01:48:48,600
Or maybe...

1267
01:48:50,600 --> 01:48:52,800
Never mind. Do not
say anything. What did we even do?

1268
01:48:53,000 --> 01:48:54,719
Did extra work stick to our hands?

1269
01:48:54,720 --> 01:48:57,760
We like our job anyway.
We handle things like this all the time.

1270
01:48:58,200 --> 01:48:59,200
Sure.

1271
01:49:00,600 --> 01:49:01,799
By the way...

1272
01:49:01,800 --> 01:49:03,360
Did you notice Burak? He is gone again.

1273
01:49:04,000 --> 01:49:06,200
He comes and goes. What is he up to?

1274
01:49:10,160 --> 01:49:11,560
They called him to the mansion.

1275
01:49:12,400 --> 01:49:13,720
I swear something is going on.

1276
01:49:14,640 --> 01:49:15,640
To the mansion?

1277
01:49:16,080 --> 01:49:17,120
You did not know?

1278
01:49:17,720 --> 01:49:18,760
How would I know?

1279
01:49:19,640 --> 01:49:20,800
You came together.

1280
01:49:21,480 --> 01:49:23,680
Yaşar, Mr. Burak is an intern here.

1281
01:49:24,000 --> 01:49:25,959
And why are you asking me these things?

1282
01:49:25,960 --> 01:49:27,760
And why am I answering you?

1283
01:49:28,880 --> 01:49:30,600
Because you trust me.

1284
01:49:31,360 --> 01:49:32,360
You trust me.

1285
01:49:32,560 --> 01:49:33,560
You do.

1286
01:49:35,280 --> 01:49:36,800
You smiled. I saw it.

1287
01:49:37,880 --> 01:49:39,600
Back to work.

1288
01:49:41,360 --> 01:49:43,440
It is just us again. All right then.

1289
01:50:01,440 --> 01:50:03,079
I wish you had let me...

1290
01:50:03,080 --> 01:50:05,760
tear Mercan apart there.

1291
01:50:06,600 --> 01:50:07,680
Look at the tantrums.

1292
01:50:08,160 --> 01:50:09,160
Look at the arrogance.

1293
01:50:09,640 --> 01:50:11,000
She took Ateş and left.

1294
01:50:11,240 --> 01:50:12,240
Enough, Aslı.

1295
01:50:12,600 --> 01:50:14,320
You have been nagging for half an hour.

1296
01:50:15,840 --> 01:50:17,600
If you had left me...

1297
01:50:18,120 --> 01:50:19,200
I would have...

1298
01:50:20,400 --> 01:50:24,240
If I had let it be, Ateş would
have fully taken Mercan’s side against us.

1299
01:50:24,600 --> 01:50:25,600
Is that what you want?

1300
01:50:29,840 --> 01:50:32,480
We dealt a heavy blow to the Yıldırıms.

1301
01:50:33,360 --> 01:50:36,560
This spark
from fire already reached Mercan.

1302
01:50:37,400 --> 01:50:39,960
She learned what her parents really are.

1303
01:50:41,200 --> 01:50:42,880
Now let us enjoy this.

1304
01:50:43,240 --> 01:50:44,480
The rest will come.

1305
01:50:45,840 --> 01:50:47,000
Let them suffer.

1306
01:50:47,880 --> 01:50:49,760
But when I see Mercan...

1307
01:50:49,880 --> 01:50:51,520
My head explodes.

1308
01:50:54,440 --> 01:50:56,000
Control yourself, Aslı.

1309
01:50:57,000 --> 01:50:58,840
The real bombs are in our hands.

1310
01:50:59,160 --> 01:51:00,280
Do not forget that.

1311
01:51:01,560 --> 01:51:02,560
Calm down.

1312
01:51:13,440 --> 01:51:16,920
I could not learn in years. Will I learn in
an hour?

1313
01:51:17,520 --> 01:51:20,280
I was not by your side
for years. That is why.

1314
01:51:21,480 --> 01:51:23,240
If someone sees...

1315
01:51:25,560 --> 01:51:27,360
I will look ridiculous here.

1316
01:51:27,880 --> 01:51:29,480
I wish you had taught me at the mansion.

1317
01:51:29,800 --> 01:51:31,880
There is no one around anyway. Look.

1318
01:51:32,600 --> 01:51:33,760
Even if there were, so what?

1319
01:51:34,280 --> 01:51:35,600
What is shameful about learning?

1320
01:51:38,160 --> 01:51:39,080
Come on.
All right. Come on.

1321
01:51:39,120 --> 01:51:40,440
All right.

1322
01:51:41,720 --> 01:51:42,720
Ugh.

1323
01:51:58,280 --> 01:51:59,760
This is too high.

1324
01:52:00,000 --> 01:52:01,000
It feels that way to you.

1325
01:52:01,080 --> 01:52:02,080
I cannot do it.

1326
01:52:02,520 --> 01:52:03,520
Mercan.

1327
01:52:04,160 --> 01:52:06,120
Where
is the stubborn Mercan who never gives up?

1328
01:52:07,080 --> 01:52:08,400
I am here.

1329
01:52:09,120 --> 01:52:10,640
I will not let you fall. Trust me.

1330
01:52:11,720 --> 01:52:14,001
Try once. If you do not
like it, you will not ride again.

1331
01:52:15,240 --> 01:52:16,240
All right.
Come on.

1332
01:52:16,640 --> 01:52:17,720
I trust you.

1333
01:52:18,200 --> 01:52:19,200
All right.

1334
01:52:19,280 --> 01:52:20,399
Hold me, okay?

1335
01:52:20,400 --> 01:52:21,040
Okay.

1336
01:52:21,280 --> 01:52:22,680
Keep your hands here.

1337
01:52:23,240 --> 01:52:24,240
Place them on these.

1338
01:52:24,680 --> 01:52:27,320
Keep your fingers on the
brake. Stop if something happens.

1339
01:52:28,200 --> 01:52:31,000
Put your feet
on the ground if you lose balance.

1340
01:52:31,360 --> 01:52:32,360
So you do not fall.

1341
01:52:32,800 --> 01:52:33,800
All right? Come on.

1342
01:52:34,000 --> 01:52:35,000
I trust you.
Hold me.

1343
01:52:35,760 --> 01:52:36,760
Okay.

1344
01:52:37,600 --> 01:52:39,759
Go a little now. I will let go.

1345
01:52:39,760 --> 01:52:42,080
Ateş, hold on. Do not let go. Ateş.

1346
01:52:42,600 --> 01:52:43,600
Slowly.

1347
01:52:43,680 --> 01:52:44,680
I am holding you.

1348
01:52:45,840 --> 01:52:46,840
Ugh.

1349
01:52:48,160 --> 01:52:48,800
Ateş.

1350
01:52:48,801 --> 01:52:49,880
I am going to fall.

1351
01:52:51,080 --> 01:52:52,240
You can do it.

1352
01:52:53,440 --> 01:52:54,800
No, I cannot ride it.

1353
01:53:08,440 --> 01:53:09,840
What did you do?

1354
01:53:10,160 --> 01:53:11,760
You said you would not let me fall.

1355
01:53:15,880 --> 01:53:17,760
I told you to put your feet down.

1356
01:53:17,920 --> 01:53:18,720
You cannot even do that.

1357
01:53:18,800 --> 01:53:21,360
I trusted you and tried this.

1358
01:53:21,440 --> 01:53:23,280
I told you it was high. You never listened.

1359
01:53:23,400 --> 01:53:24,680
I am right here.

1360
01:53:24,800 --> 01:53:25,960
You fell on me.

1361
01:53:26,480 --> 01:53:28,040
I hurt my hands because of you.

1362
01:53:28,240 --> 01:53:29,359
Let me see. Does it hurt?

1363
01:53:29,360 --> 01:53:30,680
It hurts.

1364
01:53:38,240 --> 01:53:39,400
Come on, try again.

1365
01:53:42,120 --> 01:53:43,760
You almost did it. You were not bad.

1366
01:53:45,800 --> 01:53:46,800
All right.

1367
01:53:47,160 --> 01:53:48,160
I will do it. I promise.

1368
01:53:48,600 --> 01:53:49,600
Push your foot.

1369
01:53:50,440 --> 01:53:51,440
Yes.

1370
01:53:53,080 --> 01:53:56,280
If you feel
you are falling, put your feet down. Okay?

1371
01:53:56,600 --> 01:53:57,600
Put them down.

1372
01:53:57,840 --> 01:53:59,680
Yes. Like that.

1373
01:54:00,320 --> 01:54:01,320
Come on.

1374
01:54:02,440 --> 01:54:04,320
Come on. I trust you. You will do it.

1375
01:54:05,240 --> 01:54:07,520
I will push and let go.

1376
01:54:08,120 --> 01:54:08,240
Come on.

1377
01:54:08,720 --> 01:54:10,080
You can do it.

1378
01:54:10,120 --> 01:54:11,120
Ateş.

1379
01:54:13,480 --> 01:54:14,480
Ateş.

1380
01:54:16,360 --> 01:54:17,480
Come on.

1381
01:54:17,680 --> 01:54:19,560
Do not give up. Pedal.

1382
01:54:21,280 --> 01:54:22,280
Stop.

1383
01:54:24,760 --> 01:54:25,760
I did it.

1384
01:54:26,720 --> 01:54:28,280
Faster. Faster.

1385
01:54:29,880 --> 01:54:30,880
I did it.

1386
01:54:41,200 --> 01:54:43,800
I am doing it. See?

1387
01:54:46,640 --> 01:54:47,640
I did it.

1388
01:54:47,800 --> 01:54:48,800
You did it.

1389
01:54:58,680 --> 01:55:01,040
I did it.

1390
01:55:15,320 --> 01:55:16,480
Now you ride a bit.

1391
01:55:19,080 --> 01:55:20,080
Let us see your skills.

1392
01:55:26,080 --> 01:55:27,200
Come on. Jump on.

1393
01:55:28,800 --> 01:55:30,680
Do not fall though.

1394
01:55:30,880 --> 01:55:31,880
Trust me.

1395
01:55:32,200 --> 01:55:33,920
I did. What was that earlier?

1396
01:55:35,440 --> 01:55:36,440
Like this?

1397
01:55:37,680 --> 01:55:39,160
Hold here.

1398
01:56:03,400 --> 01:56:04,400
Did you like it?

1399
01:56:52,440 --> 01:56:53,680
How was it?

1400
01:56:54,400 --> 01:56:55,400
It was so fun.

1401
01:56:58,200 --> 01:56:59,200
I told you.

1402
01:56:59,760 --> 01:57:01,400
Thank you.

1403
01:57:03,080 --> 01:57:04,080
You were a great teacher.

1404
01:57:05,280 --> 01:57:06,560
I will not pretend to be modest.

1405
01:57:07,920 --> 01:57:09,160
I am a good instructor.

1406
01:57:11,480 --> 01:57:13,360
Anything else you want to learn?

1407
01:57:18,360 --> 01:57:19,720
Actually, there is something.

1408
01:57:47,680 --> 01:57:48,800
Hey, hey.

1409
01:57:53,840 --> 01:57:56,160
Son, this door is closed to you forever.

1410
01:57:56,760 --> 01:57:57,760
Get that into your head.

1411
01:57:58,240 --> 01:57:59,320
Berat, for God’s sake.

1412
01:57:59,720 --> 01:58:02,480
For old times’ sake, at least listen to me.
Let me explain.

1413
01:58:03,360 --> 01:58:04,720
Those old days were lies, brother.

1414
01:58:06,160 --> 01:58:07,920
Berat, am I a bad person?

1415
01:58:08,240 --> 01:58:10,760
I
Am not bad. You know that. Do not do this.

1416
01:58:11,520 --> 01:58:12,520
No, I do not know.

1417
01:58:13,360 --> 01:58:15,920
Look, why I hid it in the beginning...

1418
01:58:16,280 --> 01:58:17,760
I have no idea.

1419
01:58:19,280 --> 01:58:20,720
There is no explanation for this.

1420
01:58:21,760 --> 01:58:22,760
I know that too.

1421
01:58:23,080 --> 01:58:25,000
But you would understand me.

1422
01:58:25,880 --> 01:58:27,400
Uh-huh. Sure.

1423
01:58:28,400 --> 01:58:29,680
Sure. I would understand.

1424
01:58:30,600 --> 01:58:32,520
Right? Berat would understand anyway.

1425
01:58:32,920 --> 01:58:34,240
What am I supposed to understand?

1426
01:58:35,680 --> 01:58:37,360
Berat, I beg you.

1427
01:58:37,520 --> 01:58:39,480
What favor? What favor?

1428
01:58:40,640 --> 01:58:42,520
Son, my sister hates lies and deceit.

1429
01:58:43,000 --> 01:58:44,920
Çiçek hates lies and deceit.

1430
01:58:46,680 --> 01:58:49,120
Malik, this tire will not hold a patch.

1431
01:58:49,800 --> 01:58:50,800
Move on.

1432
01:58:51,120 --> 01:58:52,600
Go, Malik.

1433
01:59:06,520 --> 01:59:07,520
He is still staring.

1434
01:59:10,920 --> 01:59:12,480
La havle ve la.

1435
01:59:39,600 --> 01:59:41,360
Watch where you are going.

1436
01:59:41,520 --> 01:59:43,000
My God.

1437
01:59:43,160 --> 01:59:45,680
I am not looking
ahead. Why are you not looking ahead?

1438
02:00:08,640 --> 02:00:10,240
Is there any head left after all this?

1439
02:00:10,960 --> 02:00:13,200
The mansion is not a mansion anymore. It is
a nightmare.

1440
02:00:13,400 --> 02:00:14,640
Nothing beats the plain truth.

1441
02:00:15,640 --> 02:00:17,520
They have not recovered for months.

1442
02:00:18,680 --> 02:00:20,800
I do not understand
what is happening to this family.

1443
02:00:21,200 --> 02:00:24,360
Mrs. Müzeyyen on one side, Uncle Haydar on
the other.

1444
02:00:25,080 --> 02:00:26,240
Mercan always pays the price.

1445
02:00:28,960 --> 02:00:30,800
Do not forget the brother’s share.

1446
02:00:33,040 --> 02:00:34,640
There is a problem with the brother too.

1447
02:00:35,800 --> 02:00:38,480
Anyway, Mercan probably will not come.

1448
02:00:38,720 --> 02:00:41,159
I was waiting for her. Tell her I left.

1449
02:00:41,160 --> 02:00:43,440
Wait. You tell her yourself when she comes.

1450
02:00:44,560 --> 02:00:47,160
Did you
wake up on the wrong side of the bed today?

1451
02:00:47,720 --> 02:00:49,640
Do not call. I will tell her. No need.

1452
02:00:49,800 --> 02:00:52,720
All right. Sorry.
I am tense and took it out on you.

1453
02:00:53,520 --> 02:00:55,440
I will tell Mercan when
she comes. Do not worry.

1454
02:00:56,560 --> 02:00:57,560
Thank you.

1455
02:00:58,160 --> 02:00:58,760
See you.

1456
02:00:59,120 --> 02:01:00,120
Take care.

1457
02:01:02,600 --> 02:01:04,280
I can call a taxi if you want.

1458
02:01:04,680 --> 02:01:06,520
No need. I already did.

1459
02:01:07,880 --> 02:01:08,880
All right.

1460
02:01:38,600 --> 02:01:42,600
Zehra, make stuffed tripe
for dinner. I will feast.

1461
02:01:43,280 --> 02:01:47,360
Start with soup, then make kadayıf.

1462
02:01:48,400 --> 02:01:52,880
Mrs. Müzeyyen, I wanted
to talk to you about something important.

1463
02:01:57,040 --> 02:02:02,200
Berat
and I have been getting to know each other.

1464
02:02:04,480 --> 02:02:06,040
Now we are taking a step forward.

1465
02:02:07,560 --> 02:02:08,560
We are getting married.

1466
02:02:12,080 --> 02:02:14,640
But I have no one, as you know.

1467
02:02:16,320 --> 02:02:20,240
I thought, so people would
not think I am alone...

1468
02:02:22,520 --> 02:02:25,920
Would it
be okay if Mrs. Binnaz came to ask for me?

1469
02:02:29,680 --> 02:02:30,680
Is that a joke?

1470
02:02:36,160 --> 02:02:39,160
Am I your mother for them to ask me?

1471
02:02:43,440 --> 02:02:45,040
You are just a servant.

1472
02:02:47,760 --> 02:02:48,760
Know your place.

1473
02:02:50,360 --> 02:02:53,680
And
you would make me deal with those riffraff?

1474
02:02:57,800 --> 02:03:01,480
You can marry or stay single. That is up to
you.

1475
02:03:03,000 --> 02:03:04,800
But never cross the line again.

1476
02:03:07,160 --> 02:03:09,240
You are right, Mrs. Müzeyyen. Forgive me.

1477
02:03:13,800 --> 02:03:17,560
Prepare the menu I said for tonight.

1478
02:03:31,080 --> 02:03:34,040
Am I your mother for them to ask me?

1479
02:04:02,080 --> 02:04:05,320
When I returned
to the mansion, questions swarmed me again.

1480
02:04:06,320 --> 02:04:09,960
Why
did he hide being my brother all this time?

1481
02:04:12,400 --> 02:04:13,920
One should try to understand him.

1482
02:04:16,280 --> 02:04:17,360
Maybe there was a reason.

1483
02:04:19,760 --> 02:04:20,960
An important reason.

1484
02:04:22,040 --> 02:04:23,320
I know, but...

1485
02:04:24,200 --> 02:04:27,720
Entering the company like that...

1486
02:04:29,040 --> 02:04:31,720
Staying silent and playing games...

1487
02:04:32,600 --> 02:04:35,319
If he had told the truth instead
of lying...

1488
02:04:35,320 --> 02:04:39,120
Maybe it would have been easier to accept.

1489
02:04:40,760 --> 02:04:42,120
He could not say it.

1490
02:04:44,680 --> 02:04:46,120
Sometimes words fail.

1491
02:04:47,840 --> 02:04:49,640
He might not have gathered the courage.

1492
02:04:51,480 --> 02:04:53,760
Maybe he wanted to say it badly.

1493
02:04:54,320 --> 02:04:55,640
But he could not.

1494
02:04:57,520 --> 02:05:01,720
It
Is not easy, but living with lies is worse.

1495
02:05:04,360 --> 02:05:07,120
Sometimes people lie for those they love.

1496
02:05:31,200 --> 02:05:32,720
Why did this come to your mind?

1497
02:05:33,800 --> 02:05:35,680
I
Thought I should learn. It might be useful.

1498
02:05:37,320 --> 02:05:39,600
I am not sure if
I am doing right by teaching you.

1499
02:05:41,400 --> 02:05:44,800
If there is nothing to
fear, there is no problem.

1500
02:05:44,960 --> 02:05:47,320
Ateş Karahan.

1501
02:05:48,520 --> 02:05:52,159
If death comes, let it come from your hand.

1502
02:05:52,160 --> 02:05:53,360
Mercan Karahan.

1503
02:05:53,600 --> 02:05:56,360
God
forbid. Do not ever say such things again.

1504
02:05:58,080 --> 02:06:00,480
Come on then. Let us start.

1505
02:06:11,720 --> 02:06:14,240
I will tell you. Listen carefully.

1506
02:06:20,120 --> 02:06:21,120
Hold the gun tight.

1507
02:06:22,360 --> 02:06:24,040
Support it from below with the other hand.

1508
02:06:27,000 --> 02:06:28,000
Like this?
Yes.

1509
02:06:29,960 --> 02:06:30,920
Trust yourself.

1510
02:06:30,921 --> 02:06:32,320
Your target is straight ahead.

1511
02:06:33,680 --> 02:06:34,840
Now shoot.

1512
02:06:36,440 --> 02:06:37,480
I am firing. Are you sure?

1513
02:06:53,720 --> 02:06:56,720
At least
you did not shoot the birds. They are safe.

1514
02:06:58,000 --> 02:07:00,120
All right. I give up.

1515
02:07:00,240 --> 02:07:01,240
No, no, no.

1516
02:07:02,240 --> 02:07:03,240
We will do it together.

1517
02:07:16,040 --> 02:07:17,040
Hold your hand tight.

1518
02:07:18,160 --> 02:07:19,160
Support it.

1519
02:07:35,240 --> 02:07:37,200
Close your left eye.

1520
02:07:38,960 --> 02:07:40,120
The target is straight ahead.

1521
02:07:42,760 --> 02:07:43,760
Let yourself go.

1522
02:08:14,560 --> 02:08:15,560
That is it.

1523
02:08:16,960 --> 02:08:17,960
You were great.

1524
02:08:27,680 --> 02:08:28,680
What happened?

1525
02:08:30,400 --> 02:08:32,000
I am so happy with you.

1526
02:08:33,320 --> 02:08:36,840
Despite everything, you make me smile.

1527
02:08:38,040 --> 02:08:39,040
I am so lucky.

1528
02:09:18,320 --> 02:09:20,160
Are you okay?

1529
02:09:20,600 --> 02:09:23,800
I am fine. I had something to do outside.

1530
02:09:27,320 --> 02:09:28,320
Really?

1531
02:09:36,200 --> 02:09:37,200
Çiçek.

1532
02:09:39,640 --> 02:09:42,280
Look, you have to listen to me.

1533
02:09:43,240 --> 02:09:46,000
I do not think I
am obliged to anything about you.

1534
02:09:46,440 --> 02:09:49,520
Is our love worth so little? Will
you ignore everything?

1535
02:09:51,080 --> 02:09:53,280
You should have thought before lying to me.

1536
02:09:55,480 --> 02:09:56,480
I will not get angry.

1537
02:09:57,800 --> 02:09:58,800
I will not get angry.

1538
02:09:59,240 --> 02:10:02,600
Please listen. Let me explain myself.

1539
02:10:03,720 --> 02:10:05,600
Fine. Explain.

1540
02:10:06,520 --> 02:10:11,000
I was
going to tell you from the start who I was.

1541
02:10:11,680 --> 02:10:15,520
But that day, remember what you said to me?

1542
02:10:20,920 --> 02:10:22,920
That is how my family is too.

1543
02:10:23,880 --> 02:10:26,920
So what are you doing? Who are you?

1544
02:10:27,840 --> 02:10:31,000
I live in Cairo, Egypt. You know that.

1545
02:10:32,960 --> 02:10:38,360
I ran away
here to see you, using school as an excuse.

1546
02:10:39,160 --> 02:10:40,359
And my family...

1547
02:10:40,360 --> 02:10:44,240
Rich people there, and so on. I would faint
here.

1548
02:10:45,720 --> 02:10:49,520
Look. We have lived with
the Yıldırıms for years.

1549
02:10:50,800 --> 02:10:53,040
I have seen rich people.

1550
02:10:53,520 --> 02:10:57,520
They look at people like insects.

1551
02:10:58,160 --> 02:11:01,400
As if they were gold and we were plastic.

1552
02:11:02,440 --> 02:11:04,920
God forbid. Let them stay away.

1553
02:11:05,760 --> 02:11:07,520
They would never approve of us.

1554
02:11:08,480 --> 02:11:11,640
No, come on. What does
it have to do with it?

1555
02:11:11,960 --> 02:11:16,480
I think not all rich people are the same.

1556
02:11:17,880 --> 02:11:20,760
What matters is richness of the heart.

1557
02:11:21,200 --> 02:11:24,160
Yes, that is true.

1558
02:11:25,360 --> 02:11:28,920
But think
about it. You are rich. I am poor.

1559
02:11:29,240 --> 02:11:32,480
No. That would not work.

1560
02:11:34,080 --> 02:11:35,720
Malik, otherwise...

1561
02:11:37,280 --> 02:11:41,040
Rich? No. I wish.

1562
02:11:41,280 --> 02:11:43,920
I am poor. Truly poor.

1563
02:11:45,560 --> 02:11:49,480
Poor girl, poor boy.

1564
02:11:50,000 --> 02:11:51,000
Fine.

1565
02:11:59,120 --> 02:12:03,880
I was afraid. Afraid of losing you.

1566
02:12:04,640 --> 02:12:05,760
That is why I stayed silent.

1567
02:12:06,800 --> 02:12:10,040
I
Could not say I was one of those you hate.

1568
02:12:11,440 --> 02:12:14,760
Then my love grew. And so did my secret.

1569
02:12:16,640 --> 02:12:19,000
But my love for you was always real, Çiçek.

1570
02:12:21,480 --> 02:12:22,800
Still, you are right.

1571
02:12:23,480 --> 02:12:26,720
No matter what, there
should be no lies between lovers.

1572
02:12:28,080 --> 02:12:30,440
I am
ready to do anything to make it up to you.

1573
02:12:31,640 --> 02:12:33,480
Anything. Just ask.

1574
02:12:46,480 --> 02:12:49,400
Are you dense or what?

1575
02:12:49,680 --> 02:12:51,360
I told you I am not available.

1576
02:12:51,760 --> 02:12:53,280
Do you not understand Turkish?

1577
02:12:54,080 --> 02:12:55,400
Shut up.

1578
02:13:14,040 --> 02:13:16,800
Put that gun down. What are you doing?

1579
02:13:18,040 --> 02:13:19,600
Enough stalling.

1580
02:13:21,520 --> 02:13:27,480
We tried to work
with you, but this will not work.

1581
02:13:28,000 --> 02:13:29,600
I do not have time to waste, Aslı.

1582
02:13:30,680 --> 02:13:32,560
Now you will tell me everything.

1583
02:13:32,960 --> 02:13:34,480
Or I will blow your mind right here.

1584
02:13:35,400 --> 02:13:37,400
Who is Ateş Karahan?

1585
02:13:40,360 --> 02:13:42,320
Why did you meddle in our lives?

1586
02:13:42,760 --> 02:13:44,720
What do you want from the Yıldırım family?

1587
02:13:47,520 --> 02:13:48,880
Tell me everything.

1588
02:13:52,120 --> 02:13:54,160
There is nothing to tell.

1589
02:13:56,360 --> 02:13:58,040
I am not joking, Aslı.

1590
02:14:44,640 --> 02:14:45,960
It was a beautiful day.

1591
02:14:47,680 --> 02:14:48,880
You learned a lot.

1592
02:14:49,840 --> 02:14:51,360
It felt really good.

1593
02:14:52,560 --> 02:14:54,400
Rest if you want.

1594
02:14:54,640 --> 02:14:56,200
Or I can bring you something to eat.

1595
02:14:56,640 --> 02:14:59,000
No. I already ate too much.

1596
02:15:03,680 --> 02:15:04,680
Mercan.

1597
02:15:07,520 --> 02:15:08,560
You said let us go.

1598
02:15:11,640 --> 02:15:13,560
We can go for a while if you want.

1599
02:15:15,920 --> 02:15:17,360
If it will help you.

1600
02:15:18,760 --> 02:15:20,480
If you feel suffocated here.

1601
02:15:23,560 --> 02:15:25,040
I forgot about it, you know.

1602
02:15:26,680 --> 02:15:28,440
It slipped my mind completely.

1603
02:15:29,360 --> 02:15:30,800
Did I age overnight?

1604
02:15:36,880 --> 02:15:37,920
Let me see.

1605
02:15:42,240 --> 02:15:43,240
A little, yes.

1606
02:15:47,120 --> 02:15:48,800
You will wait a long time.

1607
02:15:54,240 --> 02:15:56,760
I will love you at every age.

1608
02:16:02,400 --> 02:16:03,800
Can we really go?

1609
02:16:06,120 --> 02:16:12,600
We tried to escape chaos
and fell into bigger chaos, did we not?

1610
02:16:13,920 --> 02:16:15,880
While we make plans, life laughs at us.

1611
02:16:19,960 --> 02:16:22,720
The only thing that matters is you.

1612
02:16:24,120 --> 02:16:25,480
And what you want.

1613
02:16:32,040 --> 02:16:33,000
Well...

1614
02:16:33,001 --> 02:16:34,640
I am by your side.

1615
02:16:38,280 --> 02:16:40,800
I am with you. Where I should be.

1616
02:16:41,520 --> 02:16:42,920
Where I want to be.

1617
02:16:43,880 --> 02:16:45,160
That is what matters most.

1618
02:16:47,560 --> 02:16:50,160
And leaving now would not be right.

1619
02:16:51,040 --> 02:16:52,040
With all this going on.

1620
02:16:53,320 --> 02:16:54,840
I have to tell you now.

1621
02:16:55,560 --> 02:16:57,320
The longer I wait, the harder it will be.

1622
02:17:01,840 --> 02:17:02,840
Mercan. Ateş.

1623
02:17:03,240 --> 02:17:04,400
You speak.

1624
02:17:04,440 --> 02:17:05,440
You speak first.

1625
02:17:06,600 --> 02:17:07,600
Always you.

1626
02:17:13,480 --> 02:17:15,160
I know you worry about me.

1627
02:17:16,760 --> 02:17:18,440
I know you want to make me happy.

1628
02:17:20,160 --> 02:17:21,720
But I am fine. Do not worry.

1629
02:17:25,280 --> 02:17:26,400
For a long time...

1630
02:17:27,440 --> 02:17:29,400
There was a circle of lies around me.

1631
02:17:31,760 --> 02:17:32,760
Apparently.

1632
02:17:34,720 --> 02:17:36,520
You became my way out.

1633
02:17:40,440 --> 02:17:42,520
You became my hope to
believe in life again.

1634
02:17:47,880 --> 02:17:49,040
If I take another blow...

1635
02:17:49,880 --> 02:17:51,040
I cannot get back up.

1636
02:17:55,080 --> 02:17:56,360
But despite all this bad luck...

1637
02:17:57,840 --> 02:17:59,560
I am also very lucky.

1638
02:18:02,120 --> 02:18:04,840
Because I have you.

1639
02:18:05,160 --> 02:18:06,160
You are mine.

1640
02:18:07,400 --> 02:18:08,400
Your love.

1641
02:18:11,560 --> 02:18:13,320
You are the only thing I hold on to, Ateş.

1642
02:18:14,960 --> 02:18:16,200
I trust you deeply.

1643
02:18:17,480 --> 02:18:19,720
And I know you would never lie to me.

1644
02:18:45,240 --> 02:18:47,000
I trust you deeply.

1645
02:18:48,240 --> 02:18:50,520
And I know you would never lie to me.

1646
02:18:55,000 --> 02:18:57,360
What were you going to say?
